title: blender chocolate fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put first 6 ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven while center is still shaky.

title: oven french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Scrub potatoes, cut into long strips about 1/2-inch wide.
Dry strips thoroughly on paper towels.
Toss in a bowl with oil as if making a salad.
Toss with optional spices.
Spread potatoes in a single layer on a cookie sheet and place in preheated oven for 35 minutes.
Turn strips periodically to brown on all sides.
If a crispier, browner potato is desired, run under broiler for a minute or two.
Sprinkle with salt. Yield: 6 servings, 80 calories per serving.
This is a low cholesterol, reduced fat recipe.

title: aloha sandwich spread
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Drain pineapple and mix with cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve on rounds of nut bread or Ritz crackers.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a jar to store.
To make hot chocolate, mix 4 tablespoons with 1 cup of boiling water.

title: lemon squares
directions: Bake 20 minutes longer at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut in squares.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, water, and flavor packets.
Set aside.
Crush dry noodles.
Mix noodles with almonds, sunflower seeds, onions, and slaw.
Drizzle with dressing and toss.

title: pita points
directions: Cut pita bread into 8 pie-shaped pieces (like pizza).
Split sections open and pull apart.
Drizzle olive oil on "rough" side of bread.
Sprinkle with seasonings as desired.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and vanilla.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Remove and stir for 10 minutes.
(Turns to light caramel color.)
Mix together.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: In large bowl mix cereal, sugar, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in jars in refrigerator.
Grease tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: monte cristo
directions: Cut 3 slices of Italian bread.
Place 3 ounces of ham and 1 slice of Swiss cheese on first piece.
Top with another slice of bread, 3 ounces turkey and 1 slice American cheese.
Top with remaining slice of bread.
Dip sandwich into egg wash and grill like French toast.
Microwave or bake until hot through.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Wrap each roll or biscuit around a sausage link.
Follow baking instructions on can to brown.
Makes 10 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter a 1/2-quart baking dish. Spread the apples in it and sprinkle 1/3 cup water on top.
Combine the flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a bowl and rub in the butter with your fingers until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Spread evenly over the apples.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until the crust is browned.
Serve with heavy cream or whipped cream.

title: milk chocolate rice krispies
directions: Heat milk chocolate chips, oleo and syrup.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar and mix.
Add Rice Krispies.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator.
Cut into small squares to serve.
(May melt chocolate chips in microwave or double boiler.)

title: chicken livers
directions: Wrap rinsed chicken livers with strips of uncooked bacon. Place on cookie sheet.
Baste with butter and Worcestershire sauce mixture.
Broil in oven, turning once.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Put eggs in pot and cover with water; heat just until the water boils. Remove pot from heat and cover. Let stand 15 to 18 minutes; remove shells from eggs. Cut eggs in half and remove yolks. Put the yolks in a small bowl and mash with fork. Add rest of ingredients and mix. Fill the egg whites with mixture, heaping it up slightly. Hint: Set pot in sink and run cold water over them to cool eggs down quickly. This makes them easier to peel.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat milk and corn gradually.
Stir in egg.
Add next four ingredients and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch round baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable oil pie pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt in a medium bowl.
Mix oil and milk together with a fork.
Add to flour and mix with hands until just mixed.
Add a little cold water if more liquid is needed.
Split dough into two balls.
Chill 10 minutes.
On a dry floured counter, press dough into a flat circle with hands.

title: hermits
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, margarine, coffee, egg, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until almost no indentation remains when touched.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream.
Put half in a bowl and let it begin to jell.
Then cover with sour cream.
Pour on the other half which you have not chilled.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: minestrone soup casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Then dump together and season to taste: a little Tabasco, chile powder and garlic.
Great on a cold day. Serve with corn bread.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well mixed.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, frozen coconut and sour cream until blended.
Place in a covered container and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in layers.
When cool, split layers into 4 layers.
There should be enough topping to cover all four layers.
Cover entire cake and refrigerate for another day or two.
The longer this cake is refrigerated, the better it becomes.

title: fried rice
directions: Chop celery, carrots and onion.
In large saucepan, break eggs in peanut oil.
In separate corners of pan, place celery, carrots and onion.
With spatula, chop egg up and flip as it cooks and stir other vegetables.
Add rice and soy sauce and mix all together, stirring and flipping until rice is brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
In bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then add vanilla and flour.
Mix until smooth and pour over chocolate batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: good baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger or sausage, whichever you choose.
Drain. Add pork and beans and onion; simmer 10 minutes.
Good over cooked rice or mashed potatoes or biscuits.

title: oatmeal banana bread
directions: Combine bananas, oats and milk in bowl; set aside.
Cream butter or oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients, adding alternately with banana mixture to creamed mixture.
Spoon into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from pans; cool on wire rack.
Yields 2 loaves.
Can be frozen up to 3 months.

title: louisiana yam corn bread
directions: Sift flour with cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk and oil in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add yams and beat until blended.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until flour mixture is moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until breads test done.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm with butter.

title: punch recipe(club member: john waters)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. The ginger ale is to be added just before serving. Sherbet can be added if desired.

title: tortellini in garlic basil sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add basil and oregano; stir frequently and do not overcook.
Add butter; let melt.
Continue to stir.
Meanwhile, water should be brought to a boil.
Add tortellini.
Cool and toss.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat oil in skillet; brown meat; set aside.
Drain pineapple and combine the juice with the water, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Cook sauce in the skillet until clear and slightly thickened.
Add meat and cook over low heat for about 55 minutes.
Add green pepper, onion slices and pineapple chunks and simmer about 5 more minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: skillet fried corn
directions: Place bacon slices in skillet and cook until crisp; remove from skillet to cool.
For fresh corn, cut off cob (it is better cut off cream style).
Mix corn, salt and sugar; pour
into bacon drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon strips into corn.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes over low heat.
Stir often.

title: so-o good butterscotch pie
directions: Combine brown sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks and water and beat with
electric
mixer
until creamy and smooth.
Heat the can of
milk
until
hot and add the creamy mixture.
Cook until thickened; stir constantly.
When thickened, remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into an 8-inch pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cook the chicken in enough water to cover until tender.
Pick off bone, return chicken to broth.
Bring to a boil.
Thicken with flour mixture.
This amount depends on the thickness you want. Cook and stir well.
A few drops of yellow food coloring adds color.
Serve over biscuits or mashed potatoes.

title: fruity cereal squares
directions: Butter baking pan or dish (9 x 9 x 2-inches).
In large saucepan, heat gelatin (dry), corn syrup and butter to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal until evenly coated.
Pat mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Cover, chill until set, about 30 minutes. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Stores at room temperature.
Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: barbecues
directions: Mix all together and heat thoroughly.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread the can of blueberry pie filling followed by the can of crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle the box of yellow cake mix over top (don't mix).
Pour the butter over the cake mix and sprinkle with chopped pecans if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, sugar, oats and butter.
Pat in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips.
Add peanut butter.
Spread over cooled bars.
Refrigerate.

title: rigatoni with meat sauce
directions: In large saucepan heat oil. Saute onion, garlic, carrot and celery until golden brown. Add parsley, oregano, basil and meat. Stir and cook until meat is brown. Add wine and let evaporate quickly. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper; simmer about 1/2 hour. Prepare rigatoni as package directs. Drain. Pour in warm bowl. Add sauce and parmesan cheese. Toss to mix.

title: french toast with brandied lemon butter
directions: In a shallow dish, beat eggs, sugar, salt, milk and vanilla. Soak bread in mixture.
Heat butter over medium-high heat and cook each slice until lightly browned on each side.
Serve with maple syrup or Brandied Lemon Butter and lemon slices.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 6.

title: okra corn tomato medley
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add okra and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until corn is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Peel fresh carrots and cut into chunks or use frozen carrots. Boil carrots until extra soft. Drain very well. While carrots are warm, add sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Whip with mixer until smooth. Add flour and butter. Mix well. Whip eggs and add to carrot mixture. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is lightly brown. Add powdered sugar to top and serve.

title: no-knead-no-fault whole wheat bread
directions: Place the whole wheat flour in a large mixing bowl and set in the oven at the lowest temperature for 20 minutes.
While the flour is warming, dissolve the yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add the honey to the mixture and set it aside.
Then dissolve the molasses in 1 cup water.
Set aside while the flour is being warmed.
This short time period will give the yeast mixture time to work before you combine it with flour.

title: chicken vegetable fettucini
directions: Put vegetables in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish in microwave with 1 tablespoon water.
Cook until tender, then set aside to drain. Debone chicken breasts; cube and season to taste.
Brown in oleo. Remove chicken when brown, leaving remaining oleo.
Saute onions. When ready, add cheese.
When melted slowly, add milk and stir. Then add vegetables.
Stir until well coated with cheese.
Add noodles and chicken; stir gently again.
Put in same 9 x 12-inch dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: feather cake(from cookbook given to flora a. p. engle, christmas 1902.)
directions: (No directions were given; follow cake procedures.)

title: cheesy artichoke heart appetizers
directions: Unroll dough into rectangles; press onto bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread over crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with thin red pepper strips.

title: layered enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and onion, add seasonings and tomato sauce.
This may be made ahead and used when ready.
In casserole (round) alternate layers of tortillas, sauce, olives and cheese.
Add water, cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen before adding water for later use.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli, cheese, mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Heat thoroughly. (Good in crock-pot.)
Serve with plain Doritos.

title: cauliflower au gratin with almonds and cheese
directions: Boil cauliflower in salted water until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain.
Make cream sauce.
If desired, add part of cheese to sauce.
Reserve other and sprinkle over top of cauliflower.
Place whole cauliflower (or broken into flowerets) into casserole.
Pour sauce over cauliflower.
Just before serving, sprinkle with grated cheese and almonds.
Brown in moderate oven for about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cake
directions: Use a tube pan.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs together. Sprinkle flour over nuts and fruit, covering good.
Add to batter and add vanilla.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and add ground beef.
Make meatballs the size of a silver dollar and place in casserole dish. Mix the next 3 ingredients and pour over meatballs.

title: english muffins in a loaf
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry mixture and beat well. Stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle top of batter with cornmeal.
Cover, let rise in warm place for 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Turn out of pans while bread is still warm.

title: barbara's pineapple cream pudding cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Meanwhile, combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 20 minutes.
Poke fork into done cake.
Pour on pineapple mix; spread evenly.
Cool completely.

title: quick buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Work in shortening.
Add buttermilk and stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet, leaving a little space between biscuits.
Bake at 425 degrees until nicely browned, about 10-12 minutes.

title: country chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine over low heat in saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add buttermilk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Continue cooking ten minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in chives.
Reserve 2 tablespoons egg and combine remaining egg and buttermilk to flour mixture, mixing just until moistened.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough ten times.
Roll out dough to 10-inch circle.
Place over chicken mixture.
Brush with reserved egg.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon punch
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 gallons.
Add large bottle ginger ale or more if you need to make more.

title: jennie's broccoli casserole
directions: Beat egg with fork.
Add mayonnaise and chicken soup; blend well.
Stir in broccoli, onion and cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart oblong dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour and vanilla beating well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set oven at 350° and bake one hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, eggs, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 7 to 9 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Brown hamburger and onion together. Drain. Add salt, pepper, garlic, soup, chilies and enchilada sauce. Mix well. Line bottom of 13 x 9 casserole dish with tortillas. Cover with half of the meat mixture. Add another layer of tortillas, then meat sauce. Cover with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: glorified rice
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the syrup.
In a saucepan, combine rice, water, pineapple syrup and salt.
Mix just to moisten the rice.
Bring quickly to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, banana and lemon juice. Stir and then allow to cool completely.
Fold in cream.
Chill before serving.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine broth, broccoli and butter.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer 20 minutes.

title: austrian apple torte
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar to eggs slowly, 1/2 cup at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Stir in flour mixture 1/2 at a time.
Fold in apples. Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook meat, onions, pepper and seasoning in skillet until meat is brown. Put about 1/2 cup of cheese in the bottom of an unbaked pie shell.
Pour drained, cooked meat mixture over cheese in shell.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and eggs and pour over meat mixture. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, then cool for 10 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Place dough on a large cookie sheet on foil.
Pat out with hand, then sprinkle cheese.
Spread pepperoni on dough and sprinkle with olive oil and oregano.
Fold into thirds, seam faced down, on cookie sheet.
Pinch ends closed.
Bake around 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, in preheated oven, until golden brown.
Can brush crust with egg white.
Slice and serve.

title: mammas quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, add dry ingredients; cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Turn out onto floured surface; knead just to coat with flour; flatten to even thickness. With a round cutter, cut rolls and place onto a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Put into mixing bowl the yellow cake mix, vanilla pudding, sour cream, eggs and oil.
Beat as directed on package. Put half of batter into greased pan.

title: irish cream
directions: Mix first three ingredients in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: potato smoked sausage casserole
directions: Pare and slice enough potatoes to equal 2 cups; set aside. Cook onion in 1/4 cup margarine until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Place half of sausage in bottom of 2-quart ovenproof casserole.
Add half of potatoes, half of peas and half of sauce.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients, ending with sauce.
Combine crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp, crab and crawfish boil
directions: Add shrimp, crab, crawfish, corn and potatoes to pot of boiling water with shrimp boil.
Wait a few minutes (not too long) and take out.
Throw all ingredients on a table and enjoy!
A little messy but fun!

title: overnight crab casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in deep casserole dish (1 quart size). Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
May sprinkle little paprika on top.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: In skillet over medium heat, brown meat and onions.
Cook until done; drain.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and pepper.
Set aside.

title: turkey corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients except salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill milk in freezer several hours.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and undrained pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickens.
Whip margarine, cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Fold into jello.
Whip milk until it peaks.
Fold into mixture.
Butter dish and sprinkle with 1/2 of crumbs.
Pour cheese mixture.
Put remainder of crumbs on top.
Chill several hours.

title: orange spiced tea
directions: Peel oranges (no white), cut into thin strips, spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Toss all ingredients. Cover.
Store one week before use.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix sauces, spices and pork together and simmer.

title: dump cake
directions: Into a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour the can of pineapple.
Over it, spread the cherry pie filling.
Spread the coconut over this, then sprinkle the dry cake mix over all these layers.
Top with nuts. Put thinly sliced oleo over top.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Add the raisins, juice and nuts; mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
This is a nice moist cookie.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer the ingredients as stated in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with Tostitos or a heavier chip.

title: easy salad
directions: Stir gelatin into boiling water until dissolved.
Let stand until cool.
Add carrot, celery and pineapple.
Also add cheese if used.
Refrigerate until gelatin is firm.
Serves 6.

title: lamb shanks
directions: Put shanks in covered ovenproof casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and cut large onion and put slices on top of shanks. Pour all over shanks and cover your dish.
Potatoes and carrots may be added to dish.
Bake 3 hours in 300° oven.

title: diet chicken
directions: Line baking pan with foil.
Arrange chicken pieces in pan. Cover with foil.
Mix together other ingredients and sprinkle over chicken.
Place onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: mrs. lowell's thanksgiving cornbread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add corn muffin mix, sour cream, corn, melted butter and sugar.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate almond brittle
directions: In a
1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar, corn syrup and salt; mix well.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in almonds; microwave on High again 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
As soon as the mixture foams, quickly pour onto a greased metal baking sheet.
Cool completely.
Break into 2-inch pieces. Melt chocolate in microwave.
Drizzle over top.
Yield:
About 1 pound.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together well.
Pour enough boiling water just to mix well.
Add shortening.
Form into palm size pones. Deep fry until golden brown.

title: spiced roast with dijon sauce
directions: Using a mortar and pestle, crush the fennel seed, mustard seed and pepper.
Set aside.

title: barley sausage(vedaras)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fill large, clean sausage casings with mixture.
Boil in salt water or place in baking dish; bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: soup enchiladas
directions: Beat: 6 eggs, add salt and pepper.
Fry as pancakes.

title: diabetic sugarless cake
directions: Chop raisins and boil water and raisins for 5 minutes in a 2-quart pan.
Remove from heat and add apples, chocolate and margarine.
When mixture is cool, stir in flour, baking powder and soda.
Add egg, liquid sweetener (Sweet 10) and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute by hand and stir in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into pieces, wrap and store in freezer. Contains 175 calories per piece.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Do not drain the pineapple.
Mix flour, pineapple, sugar, eggs, nuts and baking soda well. Pour into a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Mix the powdered sugar, butter, cream cheese and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Spread immediately over hot cake and let cool.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Cook and chop chicken.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake in 350° oven until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: crab dip spectacular
directions: Combine and chill.
A must for Christmas.

title: punch with a punch
directions: Mix juices, lemonade and sugar.
Let stand until ready to serve.
Then add ginger ale, strawberries, sherbet, ice cubes and rum.
Enjoy!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Dredge peaches in flour.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well. Set aside.
Roll 3/4 of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Fit into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon in peach mixture.
Roll remaining pastry out to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice fashion over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix well and drop by spoonfuls into muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and remove bones.
Cook eggs approximately 10 minutes and slice. Combine milk and flour together and pour into chicken broth.
Add chicken and eggs for a delicious dinner.
Salt and pepper to your taste; serve over hot biscuits.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: crumb cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and well beaten egg.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk (start and end with flour).
Beat altogether until batter is creamy.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: godmother's flag cake(4th of july tradition)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch) jelly roll pans.
Prepare 1 package of cake mix, substituting orange juice for water.
Spread batter evenly in cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool cake for 15 minutes in pan.
Invert on rack.
Repeat steps for second cake mix.
Slice 1 pint of strawberries.
Cut remaining strawberries in half.
Beat the whipped cream, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt until stiff peaks form.
Put one cake layer on a flat serving board.
Spread with about 2 cups whipped cream and top with sliced strawberries.
Put the second cake layer on top.
Put remaining whipped cream over top and sides of cake.

title: baked stuffed eggplant
directions: Wash eggplant and cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully remove pulp, leaving 1/2-inch of the outer shell.
Dice pulp.

title: chicken breasts de duxe
directions: Dust chicken with flour.
Melt oleo in heavy skillet and add chicken.
Cook over moderate heat about 15 minutes on each side. Pour mushrooms with broth into saucepan. Add bouillon cube and heat.
Blend wine and cornstarch (to mushrooms) until thickened. Allow sour cream to come to room temperature.
Place in bowl, stir until smooth.
Add to sauce.
Remove chicken to warm place.
Pour sauce into skillet.
Heat and serve over chicken and rice on platter.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Stir ingredients until dissolved.
Beat until smooth (will be thin but will thicken later on).
Keep in refrigerator.

title: betty's breakfast casserole
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together milk, eggs, salt, mustard, pepper and onions.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: creamy chicken-broccoli soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add half and half and broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Yields 4 cups.
To store, refrigerate up to 2 days; freeze up to 1 month.

title: family special
directions: In large pot, brown hamburger.
Open macaroni and cheese box, reserve cheese package until later.
Add 2 cups water, spinach and macaroni (only, not cheese) to hamburger and bring to boil. Reduce heat, simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese package, Cheddar, partially drained kidney beans and garlic salt to taste.
Stir well.
Let "sit" 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.
May be doubled.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Work in flour.
The last bit of flour may be worked in with hands.
Add nuts.
Chill dough. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until set, but not browned.
Roll in sifted confectioners sugar while warm.
Cool.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together and freeze until a mush.
To 1 gallon of punch, add 1 quart of ginger ale.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: hot or cold tuna salad
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Mix lemon juice, mayo, mustard, sugar, basil and salt.

title: marinated potato, ham and green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well.
Let stand overnight before serving.
You may make this and keep in refrigerator for a long time as it is used.
The longer it stands, the better the flavor.

title: collard greens
directions: Steam ham hocks in a small amount of water for about 1 hour. Cut and wash collard greens very well.
Add the greens, chopped green pepper, scallions, sugar and seasoning to the pot.
Simmer for approximately 1 hour or until tender.

title: saladmaster meat loaf
directions: Use #1 blade on Saladmaster machine to grate potato, carrot, celery and crackers to a fine mesh.
Cut onion on #2 blade.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 the bottle of soy sauce.
Mix to a consistent color. Add meat and knead thoroughly to a consistent color throughout. (Check for dry spots or lumps of unmixed meat; knead some more.)

title: sausage strata
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with bread (may take more than six slices).
Spread cooked, drained sausage over bread; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well. Pour over sausage and cheese.
You can make the night before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let sit a few minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken apart and place in casserole dish.
Pour soup, celery and chicken in bowl.
Mix in one can of milk and mix good. Pour this mixture over chicken.
Melt 1 stick of butter with 1 can broth.
Mix with stuffing mix.
Spoon this mixture on top of 2nd layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie(dry bottom)
directions: Pour into 2 crusts and sprinkle flour mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.

title: mandarin orange and cashew chicken
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons syrup from oranges.
Blend reserved syrup with stir-fry sauce.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add sweet potatoes, brown sugar, margarine, spices, salt and sweetened condensed milk in a large mixing bowl; beat until fluffy.

Add evaporated milk and lemon flavoring; beat just until blended. Stir in coconut. Beat egg whites with electric mixer until foamy; gradually add white sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.

title: roll biscuits
directions: Mix warm water and yeast together.
Mix flour, sugar, soda and buttermilk. Add yeast and water.
Mix and put in icebox. Pinch
off a small piece, roll and cut out.
Bake in greased baking pan.

title: fred's pound cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and baking soda; set aside.
(Baking soda will react with buttermilk and volume will increase.) Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter (at room temperature) and sugar. Alternately add eggs, one at a time, with flour and buttermilk mixture.
Bake for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange apple slices in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour water over top.
Combine cake mix, brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon.
Stir until thoroughly blended. Mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apple slices.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve warm or cooled completely with whipped topping or ice cream, if desired.

title: milky way cake
directions: Add sugar to melted Milky Ways and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Add milk alternately. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325° (two 8 or 9-inch round pans).

title: raw potato dumplings
directions: Grate potatoes fine and drain off brown liquid. Add the beaten eggs, salt, crumbs and flour to make a stiff dough.
Drop into boiling salted water from a wet spoon.
Dumplings should be about 1 1/2-inches long and 1/2-inch in diameter when cooked.
They are done as soon as they float to the top.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Beat real good (several minutes), then add eggs, one at a time, beating each time.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to milk.
Add flour and milk alternately to other ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This cake is good plain, frosted or frozen.
Do not open oven door.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Blend apricots, coconut and pecans together in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in condensed milk.
Shape into small balls and roll colored coconut.
Let stand in air until firm.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: Heat applesauce and mix with dry Jell-O.
Measure juice of one orange.
Add enough 7-Up to make one cup.
Mix with Jell-O and applesauce.
Add grated orange rind.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: cheesy ham nuggets
directions: Combine with first 6 ingredients; mix well with fork.
Cut ham into 20 (1-inch) cubes.
Shape a thin layer of cheese mixture around each ham cube.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Yields 20 appetizers.

title: jumbo cookies
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Mix second four ingredients in another bowl until well blended.
Add mixtures together and blend well.
Add nuts and chocolate drops.
Do all blending by hand with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 13 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan until looks flaky.
Cool about 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large kettle; add next 6 ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until all vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and cheese.
Cook until soup is heated through and cheese is melted.
Yields 10 to 12 servings (3 quarts).

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat dry cake mix, margarine and egg in large bowl on low speed until blended.
Press on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown; cool.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: In heavy pan, combine chicken, roux, onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cook, covered, on low heat for about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Add green onions and parsley.
Cook another 10 minutes.
Serve with cooked white rice.

title: tea dainties
directions: Mix together butter, dates and sugar.
Cook over low flame, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Mix together egg (beaten), milk and salt.
Add to date mixture.
Cook 2 minutes and cool.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in chopped nuts or coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Mix flour and whipping cream together, then place dough on a floured pastry board. Roll out dough.
Cut out biscuits and place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: tacoed eggs
directions: In a bowl, combine eggs, cheese, onion, green pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Cook and stir in a nonstick skillet until eggs begin to set.
Add taco meat.
Cook until eggs are completely set. Spoon onto a warmed tortilla and roll.
Top with salsa.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until browned, drain meat.
In 2 qt. shallow baking dish, spread sausage.
Top with bread cubes and cheese.
Mix picante sauce, eggs, and milk and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes only 6 servings, so I double this and put in 9 x 13 baking dish for our Sunday School class.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise and layer in slightly greased casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over franks.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick turtles
directions: Arrange pecans in clusters of 3 or 4 halves, 2 inches apart, on a greased baking pan.
Top each cluster with 1 caramel, flattened slightly.
Bake at 300° for 7 minutes or until caramel softens.
Remove to wax paper.
Flatten caramels with spatula; top each candy with 1 milk chocolate square while still warm.
Spread chocolate when melted.
Refrigerate a few minutes, until chocolate hardens.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about one hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add all ingredients into glass baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Top with favorite cheese about 10 minutes before done.

title: chicken casserole no. 2
directions: Microwave chicken (cover with Saran Wrap) for 10 minutes or more, depending on microwave.
Layer bottom with 1 package of crackers (crumbled).
Add cut-up chicken.
Mix together soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Top with crumbled crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bread.
Hollow out inside of 1 loaf of rye bread.
Put dip in bread.
Use excess bread and the other loaf of bread for dipping.

title: corny biscuits
directions: Mix together and drop teaspoonfuls onto a baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Beat shortening, sugar and molasses until creamy.
Beat in egg yolk.
Blend in flour mixture.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll dough 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut into shapes.
Place 1/2-inch apart
on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cookies may be decorated before or after baking, as desired.

title: beaten biscuits
directions: Beat forty-five minutes on a block with an axe.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Put 1/2 of cheese in cooled pie crust.
Sprinkle drained sausage on cheese.
Pour eggs and milk on cheese.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30-45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: cheese filled coffee cake
directions: Mix yeast, water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add egg.
Cut margarine into flour and salt.
Mix well. Add yeast mixture.
Divide into 2 balls.
Roll each into an 8 x 10-inch rectangle.

title: water chestnuts wrapped in bacon
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnuts.
Secure with a toothpick. Blend remaining ingredients, set aside.
Broil bacon wrapped water chestnuts until bacon is crisp.
Drain and place in oblong dish. Pour sauce over cooked chestnuts and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: bert's peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Put sugar and syrup in a microwaveable bowl and cook on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and cook for 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and cook for 1 more minute.
Take out of microwave and add baking soda.
Stir and pour into a buttered pizza pan.
Cool.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: In a small skillet heat a small amount of oil and brown the onions.
Add the ground beef and brown.
Drain off the fat. Cook the macaroni according to the package and drain.
Add the beef to the mixture, along with the soup.
Heat through.
Transfer to a casserole dish to serve.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2 pan with Pam.
Beat eggs until foamy in large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and Crisco (butter) until creamy.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts at low speed (mixture will be stiff). Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cool 10-15 minutes and cut into bars.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips, for 2 minutes.
Add chips. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: summer fruit cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs (one at a time) and soda in buttermilk. Add flour.
Chop and flour dates, nuts and orange slices, cut up.
Add to mixture. Cook at 250° for 2 3/4 hours.
Mix orange juice and sugar.
Pour over cake and let stand overnight.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin into bowl.
Chop onion and add to bowl.
Mix salad dressing, sugar, fresh ground pepper and parsley until creamy in separate bowl.
Add to cucumber and marinate for at least two hours in refrigerator.

title: cauliflower morocco
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter with juice of 1 lemon. Saute cauliflowerets in butter with garlic, basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: walnut butter crunch
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add sugar, stirring constantly until dissolved.
Add water and syrup.
Cook on low until brittle (290°).
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts.
Spread in greased jellyroll pan; cool until hard.
Melt chocolate and pour over crunch; sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Elevate pan to cool so it doesn't continue to cook.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over squash, onions and peppers.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain well.
Bring remaining ingredients to a full boil.
Pack in sterile jars.
Seal.

title: chicken bake
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk, chicken broth or half and half.
Cook until thick.
Add the chicken mixture (chicken, peas, pimientos and mushrooms); season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour into a large shallow baking dish.
Cover top with 1 1/2 inch baking powder biscuits, press a slice of stuffed olive in center of each and bake at 450° for 12 to 18 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: cold peach soup
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until frothy.
Pour into soup bowls.
Garnish with nutmeg and mint sprigs.
Serve as a side dish to any spicy entree.

title: seven-up cake and icing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread pudding
directions: Mix bread crumbs, egg whites and skim milk together.
Mix in cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour in dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
High in nutrition.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in 1 quart slightly salted water for 20 minutes. Drain and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Add other ingredients. Beat with eggbeater only until blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until knife comes out clean.

title: jalapinto rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in pinto beans, rice and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pudding in pineapple juice until dissolved.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk (do not boil).
Stir in margarine, cornmeal and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cornmeal comes away from sides of pan and thickens.
Set aside.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Fold in beaten egg white. Mix gently but thoroughly. Pour into a greased, floured baking dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: 24 hour layered salad
directions: Layer each in order.

title: meat loaf casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening until red disappears.
Add chopped onion, green pepper, parsley, catsup, steak sauce, tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, onions, sour cream, soup, margarine and cheese together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Mix cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: ham with gingered pineapple
directions: Bake ham on rack in roasting pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until thermometer registers 140°.
Blend juice from pineapple with sugar, soy sauce, ginger and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Twist pineapple slices and arrange on ham.
Brush sauce over pineapple and ham.
Bake 30 minutes longer, brushing with remaining sauce after 15 minutes.

title: mexitalian lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine chili, drained salsa, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
In small bowl, stir cottage cheese and parsley flakes.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, chili mixture and Mozzarella cheese in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray; repeat to make three layers.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lasagna is thoroughly heated.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook meat and drain well.
Spread on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper in bowl with wire whip.
Add onion and pepper; pour over top of meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm in middle.

title: hermits
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Cream butter and add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix other ingredients and add to butter and eggs in 2 or 3 portions, mixing until smooth.
Drop 2 inches apart on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam by teaspoonfuls.
Bake 10 minutes or until nicely browned.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart on greased foil lined baking sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from baking sheets immediately or they will stick if allowed to cool on pan. Store, covered, at room temperature.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Dump fruit filling in cake pan.
Sprinkle some cinnamon over evenly.
Add dry yellow cake mix.
Place pats of butter evenly on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Bake at 375°.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix peas, asparagus and soup and put in casserole bowl.
Slice margarine in small pieces and put on top.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Put in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: catalina shell salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add dressing and marinate in refrigerator with dill weed, preferably overnight.
Add onions, tomatoes and cucumber.
Salt and pepper to taste; mix together well.
Serve chilled.

title: old time fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa, salt and syrup to soft ball.
Set aside and cool to lukewarm.
Add to fudge the butter and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Pour on buttered platter.

title: fruit filled squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine, sugar and extracts; add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour and baking powder; add to dough.
Mixture will be very thick and stiff.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Place 1/2 of batter in pan; spread with spatula. Spread can of pie filling on batter.
Drop rest of batter by spoonfuls, leaving space between; batter will spread during baking.
Bake 35 minutes until top is browned and tests done. Cool in pan on rack and cut in squares or bars.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients in order given, mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add meat and cook, breaking up. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, sauce mix and V-8 juice.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: frosted toffee bars
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oats, sugar and margarine; mix well. Spread in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 13 minutes, or until light golden brown; cool.
In a small, heavy saucepan over low heat (or in microwave), melt chips.
Spread over oat mixture; sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until chocolate is set.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 dozen bars.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add cream, egg and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add apples and pour into unbaked pie shell. Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon and cut in butter.
Sprinkle this topping on pie.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over 100% Bran and mix in order given.
Mixture may be stored in airtight container and baked when needed.
Bake in greased muffin pans.
Grease lightly even if they are teflon lined.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Use a 3-quart saucepan.
Fill 3/4 full of water.
Add chicken broth or bouillon cubes.
Finely chop carrot, onion and celery; add to water and cook until tender.
Add cheese.
When cheese melts, stir in cornstarch, mixed with small amount of water. Serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Cool. Remove meat from bone in small chunks.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 cup milk with 1 can of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle water chestnuts over chicken.
Pour 1/2 cup chicken broth over cornbread stuffing mix and stir.
Put on top of casserole and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: christmas braid
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little warm water.
Mix shortening, salt, sugar, egg, vanilla and milk.
Add yeast mixture, then flour.
Mix well.
Add raisins, candied fruit and nuts.
Let rise.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll each portion into a long roll.
Form into a braid.
Let rise until light.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add the next 2 ingredients and refried beans. Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with tortilla chips.
Spread meat mixture. Layer chilies and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with taco fixings, such as chopped lettuce, tomato, black olives, sour cream, etc.
I top it with crumbled tortilla chips.
Enjoy.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar in a bowl and mix.
Add eggs. Measure and sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice together.
Add to shortening, sugar and eggs, then add milk and jam.
Pour into two greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Put apples in bowl and add next 5 ingredients.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for minutes.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: In a 2 quart casserole dish place in layers:

title: matilda's divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt to 250° on candy thermometer.
Put Marshmallow Creme in large bowl. Pour sugar syrup slowly over Creme while stirring. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices; mix well with egg mixture.
Add raisins, nuts and water.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool completely before cutting.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together and then put into graham cracker crust shell.
You may sprinkle a few graham cracker crumbs on top. Do not freeze. Chill in the refrigerator for a few hours.
Serves 1 to 4.

title: rice stroganoff
directions: In
a 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add mushrooms, scallions and
garlic
and	saute over medium heat until mushrooms are just tender, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except rice
and sour cream and bring mixture to a boil. Add rice
and stir to combine.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook until	liquid is
absorbed
and rice is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir	in sour cream and serve immediately.
Healthy. Makes 4 servings with 160 calories per serving.

title: versatile french dressing
directions: For pizza sauce, add oregano and basil.

title: mamma mia basic pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add oil.
Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Add yeast mixture and knead until smooth (approximately 10 minutes).
Cover.
Let rise in warm place, approximately 2 hours (until double in size).

title: mustard greens
directions: Prepare mustards for cooking by stripping the stalk out. Wash leaves thoroughly and cut them up.
Add to pot.
Fry out your salt pork in pot you are going to cook the mustards.
Add water and sugar; cook until tender.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 5 dry ingredients together.
Mix oil and sugar separately.
Add the eggs and vanilla; stir.
Add dry ingredients to oil, sugar and egg mixture, then add apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat; add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add cereals and coconut. Mix.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove quickly; cool on rack.
Do not overcook.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix in bowl on high the shortening, butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until it tastes more like butter than sugar, about 5 minutes.
Then add rest of the ingredients by hand.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: apricot nectar pound cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Mix together and put in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until springs back when touched.

title: chinese lemon chicken
directions: Combine dry jello, garlic salt and mustard.
Add melted margarine.
Mix well.
Place mixture in oblong baking dish. Arrange chicken in single layer, turning to coat both sides. Sprinkle with almond slices; cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, basting once.
Remove cover; baste again and bake 15 more minutes or until done.

title: mushroom bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent roll dough into triangles.
Place on cookie sheet; pinch seams together.
Toss sliced mushrooms in melted butter to coat.
Arrange mushrooms on top of dough.
Sprinkle with cheese and Italian seasoning.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into wedges or squares.
Serve warm. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: In small pieces, tear apart dried beef.
Mix together both cheeses, dried beef and onions.
After mixed together, form into a small ball and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour, or until ready to serve.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients and bake slowly in 325° oven for 1 hour or until firm.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and add a large can of water.
May use a juice can.
Stir.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: orange salad
directions: Add jello to fruit, then add cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Blend well and chill about 2 hours.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add beer to desired consistency. Excellent for fish or vegetable batter.
Deep fry at 350°.

title: taco party tray
directions: Blend avocado, cream cheese, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and salt.
Spread evenly on dinner plate.
Layer the rest of the ingredients on top.
Serve with chips.

title: jordan marsh blueberry
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add berries. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in greased muffin pans.

title: easy making cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Beat in syrup and vanilla.
Sift and beat in flour and baking powder. Stir in oatmeal and coconut.
Use greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: kraut slaw
directions: Mix kraut, onion, bell pepper, celery and pimentos.
Pour sugar over vegetables and stir.
Cover and refrigerate overnight (24 hours).
Next day, drain real good, stir to help with the draining.
When drained good, add the oil and vinegar.
Keep covered, will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: hot deviled potatoes
directions: Prepare 2 servings potatoes to package directions.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 2 foil baking shells. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Makes 2 servings.

title: divinitygreely, colorado
directions: Boil syrup, water and sugar until it spins a thread.
Pour over beaten egg white and continue beating until gloss is gone. Add vanilla and walnuts.
Pour onto greased platter to cool.

title: chicken wing appetizers
directions: Place chicken wings in single layer in shallow roasting pan. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Heat on top of stove until sugar is dissolved.
Pour sauce over chicken wings.
Place, uncovered, in a 350° oven and bake for approximately 2 hours. Turn wings occasionally.
After first hour, check frequently to prevent burning.
Wings are done when sauce is thick and bubbly.

title: nacho bisque potatoes
directions: Place Tater Tots in a 9 x 12-inch dish or pan.
Pour the cheese soup that has been mixed with the milk over the potatoes. Next, pour the tomato bisque soup that has been mixed with the water over the nacho cheese soup.
Mix soups with spoon gently (do not disturb potatoes).
Bake in a 350°
oven for 1/2 hour or so until Tater Tots test soft and are lightly browned and soups are thickened.
Serve hot.
Stir, slightly, when removed from the oven and ready to serve.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and set aside.
In large mixing bowl beat egg whites until foaming.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla extract. Beat until very stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, and continue to beat.
Using spatula, fold in flour.
Pour batter into 10-inch ungreased tube pan.
Using a knife, pop bubbles.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a microwave or in a double boiler on the stovetop, melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine together.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal and stir until all is coated.
Put confectioners sugar in a clean bag and pour in cereal.
Close bag and shake until all cereal is covered.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat. Drain fat. Place sausage in a greased 2 quart casserole dish.

title: chicken pasta skillet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, combine soup, milk and mustard.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Stir in broccoli.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook for 5 minutes, or until broccoli is tender.
Stir in pasta and chicken.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with red pepper slices.

title: apple pandowdy(sugar free)
directions: Peel, core and slice apples; place in bottom of 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine flour, salt, vinegar and water in saucepan and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, butter and brown sugar replacement; pour mixture over apple slices.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; split to make 3 layers.
Dissolve Jell-O in two cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups strawberries, juice and strawberry glaze.
Place in refrigerator until mixture thickens.
Mix pudding as directed.
Place 1 layer of cake in bowl, layer of Jell-O mixture and a layer of pudding.
Repeat until all is used.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: molasses oatmeal pancake or waffle
directions: Heat milk
and molasses in saucepan to 110°.
Pour over oatmeal
in
large mixing bowl.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake as
directed
in waffler or as pancake until bubbly; toss and bake until golden.

title: aunt emma's chicken and dressing
directions: Debone cooked chicken and place in large casserole dish.
Mix together soups, onions, celery and pour over chicken.
Then mix sage, dry corn bread mix, milk, and eggs.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Then add 3 cups chicken broth over this.	(Looks like too much.)	Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix together ingredients and refrigerate.
Let set until chilled.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cut cake in half when cool.
Crumble half in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix one box instant pudding mix with milk as directed and pour over cake.
Drain 1 can crushed pineapple and pour over pudding.
Spread 1 can cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Spread 1 tub Cool Whip over cherry pie filling.
Repeat entire process and top with nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: shrimp santa fe
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp or fish and picante sauce. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes. Stir in shrimp or fish. Continue to bake for another 30 minutes. Add picante sauce. Bake for 30 more minutes. Serve with rice and toasted French bread.

title: brown sugar franks
directions: Wrap each frank with a slice of bacon.
Marinate in mixture of butter and brown sugar overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into bite sizes and secure with toothpick.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Mix together turkey, eggs, mushrooms, celery, almonds and onion.
In another bowl, mix together the soup and Miracle Whip. Toss with the turkey mixture and turn into a two-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with chow mein noodles.

title: cranberry pear crisp
directions: In lightly greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, thoroughly mix cranberries, pears, granulated sugar, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon of flour; set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix remaining 3 tablespoons flour with the brown sugar.
With a pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats and nuts; sprinkle evenly over fruit mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before serving.
Serve plain or with milk.
Serves eight.
Per serving without milk:
331 calories, 4 g protein, 52 g carbohydrates, 14 g fat, 74 mg sodium.

title: honey cake
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift with baking powder, baking soda, spices and salt.
Beat eggs until thick and light, about 5 minutes.
Add sugar gradually, beating well. Add honey, coffee and shortening.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of greased and waxed paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes, then turn out on rack.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 24 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add together sugar, eggs and oil; stir. Add cinnamon, salt and baking soda; stir. Add flour and mix well. Add apples and nuts. Pour into baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: warmed oysters
directions: Have oysters opened at market.
Place oysters in deeper half shell in aluminum foil pan.
Cut lemon juice to each oyster.
Add small amount of water to bottom of pan.
Cover with aluminum foil. Barbecue over low direct heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients well. Stir in pecan pieces. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes depending on oven or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: penuche candy
directions: Combine and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat in 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool.

title: bean hamburger dish
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger.
Add onions.
Mix other ingredients except beans.
Drain kidney beans and rinse.
Drain butter beans. Add them and the pork and beans to rest of mixture.
Can be cooked in crock-pot or roaster.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape into eggs; dip in chocolate.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Gather approximately 10 beans into a bundle and wrap with 1/2 bacon strip.
Lay seam side down in glass 9 x 13 inch pan. Continue making bundles until pan is full.
Top with marinade, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until soft.
Set aside.
Heat soups and Cheez Whiz.
Add rice and broccoli to vegetables.
Add soup to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy quick tamale pie
directions: Put all ingredients in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in fat.
Add ground beef and brown.
Place uncooked noodles over beef.
Combine juice and seasonings.
Pour over noodles.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add green pepper. Cover and cook 10 minutes more.
Stir in sour cream before serving.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Very good with chili.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie pan (10 x 1 1/2-inches). Cook and
stir
beef
until
brown;
drain.
Stir in oregano, basil, tomato
paste and 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in pan.	Spoon beef mixture over
top. Beat
milk,
Bisquick
mix,
eggs, salt and pepper until smooth, 1 minute with mixer.	Pour into pan.	Bake until knife
comes
out clean,
30	to
35	minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cool 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: anne's chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Place sugar, brown sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in bowl; mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Gradually add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Add chocolate chips and blend into mix with a spoon.
Spread onto a 12 x 14-inch baking pan (greased).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until edges are lightly browned.
Cool and then cut into squares. Keep in airtight container.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Put pineapple in a pan and bring to a boil.
Add jello and mix well.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well. Pour into a large dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together hash browns, onions, cheese, sour cream, soup, one stick margarine (melted) and pepper to taste.
Cover top with bread crumbs and pour other stick of margarine, melted, over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix the persimmon pulp with the soda.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Beat oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add chocolate and instant coffee. Mix well.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Bake in lower third of oven for 25 minutes at 375°.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: fried chicken
directions: Rinse the chicken and pat dry.
Place the flour, salt, pepper, cinnamon, nutmeg and garlic powder in a shallow baking dish; stir to distribute all the ingredients evenly.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and spread into an 8 x 8-inch square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for around 40 minutes. Recipe may be doubled for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: green pepper pickles
directions: Wash peppers.
Stem and cut into lengthwise strips, discarding seeds.
Mix 4 cups vinegar and 1 cup water.
Pack pepper strips into jars, cover with vinegar mixture, add 1 tablespoon salt to each jar and put on lid tightly.
Invert for 1 hour; then store. Ready for use in 3 months.
Keeps unopened and unrefrigerated for more than 2 years.

title: patio potato salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine milk, sugar, vinegar, 1 egg, butter, cornstarch, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; blend in onion and mayonnaise.
Cool.
Combine potatoes and hard-cooked eggs; carefully fold in dressing.
Chill.
Just before serving, sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Cut shortening in until fine.
Stir in milk to a soft dough.
Knead slightly on a floured board.
Roll out and cut or pat into shape. Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a 2 1/2-quart bowl; set aside. Combine butter, cocoa and cola in a 2-cup glass measuring cup. Microwave at High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir cola mixture into flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, egg, soda, vanilla and marshmallows; beat well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread marshmallows evenly in batter.
Microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes; rotate dish 1/4 turn at 2-minute intervals.
Frost cake while hot with Chocolate Cola Frosting.

title: pinch coffeecake
directions: Put rolls in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and pudding. Dribble butter over all.
Let rise overnight.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Boil tomatoes and sugar 20 minutes.
Add Jell-O.
Boil 1 minute.
Put into jars/containers and refrigerate.

title: small chocolate pie
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Beat eggs; add dry ingredients a small amount at a time and mix thoroughly.
Add to heated milk; cook until thickened.
Take off heat; add chips, butter and vanilla.
Have ready small baked pie crust.
Beat remaining egg whites (1 additional egg white will make more meringue); add 1 tablespoon sugar for each egg white.
Pour chocolate mixture in pie crust; top with meringue and bake until brown in 250° oven.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt and pecans and set aside. Melt butter; add sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, then add dry ingredients and mix.
Pour into pan and place chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: molasses oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream the shortening.
Beat in sugar. Blend in egg and molasses. Beat well. Stir in sifted ingredients. Fold in raisins and rolled oats. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on lightly greased or Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute. Remove to cooling rack.

title: harvest loaf cake
directions: Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour with soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter and sugar; cream well.
Blend in eggs; beat well.
At low speed, add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with dry.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Let stand at least 6 hours before slicing.

title: kahlua cheesecake
directions: For crust, blend cookie crumbs with 1/3 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly over bottom and halfway up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix and shape into ball.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, spread cocktail sauce on ball.
Serve with crackers.
This appetizer is so easy and great for entertaining.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding according to directions on box.

Add the sour cream and mix well. Add 1/2 container Cool Whip and mix well. Layer pudding, bananas, cookies and continue layering in this manner until all pudding is gone. Top the entire pudding with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate. (The colder, the better.)

title: texas pecan pie
directions: This recipe will make 1 deep pecan pie or 2 small pecan pies.

title: honey butter
directions: Whip together butter and yolks.
Gradually add honey and vanilla; beat until quite stiff.
Store in refrigerator.
Use on fruit bread, French toast, waffles and pancakes.

title: potato cheese balls
directions: Combine cheese, salt and potatoes.
Form into balls.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Dip in egg, blended with milk.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and shred.
Put on inside of crescent roll and roll up.
Mix soup and milk together.
Put crescent rolls in baking dish and pour soup mixture over.
Put cheddar or american cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Sprinkle chicken with season salt. If using mushrooms, lay a slice on the tenderloin and roll up. Wrap a slice of bacon around the bundle and secure with a toothpick.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package. Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour into baking dish.
Using same pan, make a sauce with 2 tablespoons butter, milk and soup. Add shredded cheese until melted. Add sauce to vegetables. Toss and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can be made ahead.
Refrigerate and bake when ready.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook cut up onions in oil until soft.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: good dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: cajun chicken strips
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bag; add chicken and shake. Cook in butter 8 to 10 minutes.

title: copper carrots
directions: Boil carrots briefly in salted water until barely tender. Drain.
Slice onion and pepper and layer with carrots.
Mix all remaining ingredients and heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables and store in refrigerator.
Serve cold.
Keeps several weeks.

title: reese imposters
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler or microwave.
Spread over dough.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: the magic muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter 8 muffin cups.
Mix oat bran, baking powder, cinnamon and salt (optional) in a bowl.
Stir in almonds.
In separate bowl combine milk, egg, honey and chopped apple.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add milk mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place ground beef in casserole dish with onion.
Place potatoes on top. Mix cream of chicken soup with 1/2 can of water; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Cook chicken in water with tomatoes for about 45 minutes. Remove bones and skin from chicken and cut into small pieces.
Put chicken back into the broth and add all ingredients except milk. Cook over medium-low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally to avoid sticking.
Add milk when done.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk.
Add enough milk to form balls.
Drop from teaspoon into hot fat.
Cook until well browned and cooked through.
Serve hot.

title: cran-ale punch
directions: Mix
cranberry
juice and lemonade in large punch bowl. Just before serving, pour in ginger ale.
Serves 25.

title: homestyle macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix other ingredients with macaroni.
Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moma's pecan pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add crushed pecans to top of mixture and dot with butter. Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: grated sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix syrup and milk in a large bowl; add potatoes.
Beat eggs and butter.
Combine 2 mixtures.
Add other ingredients and mix. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Serves 12.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into baseball size balls. Place in shallow baking dishes, sprayed with Pam.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Glaze with Brown Sugar Glaze below and bake 20 minutes.
Makes 12 meatballs.
Leftovers can be frozen and are great microwaved.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 3325 degrees.
In large mixing bowl beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugar, and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels. Pour into pie shell and bake 55 to 60 mins.

title: corny bean casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except margarine and crackers.
Mix the melted margarine and the crushed Ritz crackers. Put this mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except walnuts.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Put in icebox to set.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and syrup. Bring to a boil over low heat. Beat eggs gradually. Add syrup mixture. Mix in nuts, salt and vanilla. Pour into crust and bake about 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter waldorf salad
directions: Toss ingredients together.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with dressing.

title: chippy blond brownies
