directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in the chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until set.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in boiling salted water.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Shrimp are done when they are pink and tender. Drain and rinse with cold water, then chill.
Make alternate layers of shrimp and onion rings in a sealable container.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over shrimp and onions.
Seal and place in refrigerator for 6 hours or more, shaking or inverting occasionally.
Drain and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: one dish meal
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole. Spread rice on bottom.
Mix flour, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Spread over rice.
Dot with 1/2 tablespoon butter.
Mix beef and onions and put over rice. Repeat. Pour over the layers the tomatoes with liquid. Spread corn on top and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Better if stands for awhile.

title: mexican squash
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet. Add onion and cubed pork. Cook until pork is tender. Add other ingredients.
Season with garlic salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a large baking pan.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: delicious muffins
directions: Add dry ingredients to egg and milk.
Just before blended, add melted shortening.
Fold in cereal.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in bread pans.

title: silky meringue
directions: Beat with an electric mixer on high speed for 1 minute or until soft peaks form (tips curl) when beaters are lifted out.
A hand mixer works fine but beating time may be slightly longer.
At soft peak stage, add sugar slowly while beating egg whites, so that sugar dissolves.
Beat 7 minutes or until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Spread the meringue over hot pie filling to avoid leakage between filling and meringue.
Also, seal the crust well to prevent leakage and shrinking.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings; mix well.
Form in single loaf in 4 3/4 x 8 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
In 30 minutes, spread some ketchup on top and continue baking.
Or, the recipe calls for a Piquant sauce that can be spread on meat loaf before you bake it.

title: crab on deck
directions: Put margarine and cheese in bowl; microwave until soft.
Drain crab.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread onto English muffins; partially freeze them.
Cut into pieces and freeze for appetizers. When ready to eat, broil until golden and eat.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in pan.
Boil and cook 5 minutes (candy thermometer, 250°) and add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well. Bake in a 225° oven for 1 hour, stirring at 15 minute intervals.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and slice when cool enough.
Chop onions fine; add to warm potatoes.
Dice bacon and fry crisp.
Remove from grease and put on the warm potatoes.
To the grease, add the flour and brown slightly.
Add the rest of the ingredients and boil until thick.
Pour over potatoes and stir well.
Best if served warm.
This will serve 15 to 20 people.

title: individual ham loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form it in small loaves in shallow pan.
Mix brown sugar, water, mustard and vinegar to make a sauce.
Pour sauce over; cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil.
Baste a couple times with sauce.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all
of the ingredients into a blender and mix well until ice cubes are crushed.

title: cinnamon ring cucumbers
directions: Soak cucumbers for 24 hours in lime and enough water to cover. Drain and soak for 3 hours in clean clear water.
Drain.
Simmer for 2 hours in 1 cup white vinegar, red food coloring and enough water to cover.
Drain.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Dissolve each box of jello in 1 cup of hot water and 3/4 cup of cold water and pour into square cake pans; let set.
Cut in 1/2 inch cubes.
Soften gelatin in cold water and dissolve in hot pineapple juice; let thicken slightly.
Whip cream, add sugar and vanilla, combine with gelatin and pineapple juice and fold in jello cubes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef; add all ingredients and warm.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook chuck with onion and pepper until done; drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a crock-pot; turn on high until well heated, then turn on low and cook 4 to 5 hours.

title: mushroom sandwiches
directions: Saute mushrooms with butter or margarine.
Add the cream and salt to taste.
Thicken with flour (mix flour with water). While cooking, add the Worcestershire sauce to hot mixture and then refrigerate overnight to thicken.
Use to make tea sandwiches.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain pickle slices and return pickles to jar. Boil sugar, vinegar and celery seed. Pour over dill slices. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: american flag cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 by 13-inch baking dish with pound cake slices. Top with 1 c. of the strawberries and 1 c. of the blueberries. Then spread cool whip on top evenly.
Use the remaining strawberries to make the strips of the flag and the remaining blueberries to make the stars of the flag.
Chill and enjoy OLD GLORY!-

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in soup in top of double boiler or crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Yields approximately 3 pints.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Using a large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Use 1 tablespoon grease to saute onion.
Add Worcestershire sauce, horseradish and catsup and stir.
Add lima beans, tomato soup and bacon bits.
Stir well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.
Very tasty.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Butter shallow 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix together sugar, flour and 3 tablespoons of the drained pineapple juice (it makes a paste). Pour in casserole and spread. Place pineapple chunks on top of paste. Cover pineapple with cheese. Mix cracker crumbs with melted margarine and sprinkle on top of cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: red raw onions
directions: Cover onions with cold water. Let stand 1 hour, changing water every 15 minutes (this takes the bite away from raw onion). Drain. Mix rest of ingredients. Put into 2-quart covered dish or jar. Chill at least 24 hours, stirring occasionally to mix well. Makes 2 quarts. Good with steak and good in sandwiches.

title: hot and spicy shrimp
directions: Mix butter and oil in flame-proof baking dish.
Add all spices and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil, then decrease heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and let the flavors marry for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine all together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°.
Later cover with egg whites.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Set aside. Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil, sugar and sour cream.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour half of brown sugar/cinnamon mixture over cake batter.
Add remaining cake batter and then remaining brown sugar mixture.
With fork, swirl brown sugar/cinnamon mixture into batter several times.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and vanilla; pour on top to glaze.

title: blanche's pickle ginny
directions: Let green tomatoes stand overnight; drain, then peel tomatoes; grind peppers, celery, cabbage and onions.
Add brown sugar, horseradish, pepper, mustard seed and vinegar.
Boil 15 minutes and seal in hot jars.

title: vegetables confetti
directions: Cover bottom of an 11 x 17-inch ungreased pan with rolls spread out flat.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix; spread over baked rolls.
Mix diced vegetables together; sprinkle over the cream cheese mixture. Cover with plastic wrap; press vegetables down into cream cheese. Keep covered.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Cut into small bars.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix together oil, cake mix, eggs and mandarin oranges.
Pour batter into greased and floured cake pans (2 or 3).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (about 20 minutes if using 3 layers) or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks.

title: white bread and cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add 1 tablespoon of sugar. Let stand in a warm place for 45 minutes.
Beat in the remaining ingredients, adding flour gradually.
Place in a well-greased bowl. Let stand until doubled in size; knead well.
Shape into loaves or rolls.
Let rise again approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 3 - 8 inch layers, 2 - 9 inch layers or 1 - 9 x 13 2 cake.
Bake at 325° until done.
Cool cake well before icing.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake your choice of yellow cake.
While cake is baking, put evaporated milk, flavoring and sugar in a measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Whip by hand.

title: double batch chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and egg until light and fluffy.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in nuts and chips. Drop from a teaspoon on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 100.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage in frying pan.
Drain off fat. In saucepan, melt the Velveeta.
Once melted, add soup and Ro-Tel. Pour ingredients from saucepan to a crock-pot.
Stir in meat mixture and chopped onion.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: anne's italian biscuits
directions: Make a well in flour and mix in remaining ingredients.
Divide dough in half.
Make 2 long loaves and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cut in diagonal slices.
Return to a cookie sheet, laying slices on cut side. Return to oven to toast approximately 5 minutes.

title: apple caramel salad
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and juice.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump above ingredients in order into a ungreased 11x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Drain pineapple and add to cream cheese.
Use 7-Up to mix Jell-O in place of cold water.
Mix cream mixture in Jell-O.
When Jell-O begins to harden (or congeal) sprinkle nuts on top or in cream mixture.
Place in refrigerator until firm and ready to serve.
Orange Jell-O is also good with this.

title: crazy pie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Blend in shortening and water.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed with electric blender. Pour batter into a 9-inch pie pan.
Do not spread.
Pour favorite pie filling in center of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 425° preheated oven.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, sugar, and cocoa in ungreased 2 quart pan (9 x 9). In a small bowl mix milk, butter, and vanilla; add to flour mixture and stir with a fork until mixed and smooth. Stir in nuts and spread the dough evenly in the pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour hot water over batter. Do not stir. Bake for 40 minutes.

title: scrod putanesca
directions: In saucepan or large skillet, add oil and garlic; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients, except scrod and angel hair; simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Wash scrod in cold water and towel dry.
Add to tomato mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cover bottom of dish with slices of beef.
Wrap 1 strip of bacon around rolled half of chicken breast.
Put 8 pieces of breast in casserole or pan which has been lined with 1 layer of beef.
Mix sauce of sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 hours at 300°.
The bacon and beef will be almost absorbed and chicken crisp, brown outside and succulent inside.

title: hermits
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, coffee, egg, soda, salt and spices.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about ten minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Beat eggs and mix with broccoli, soup, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Add melted margarine with ground crackers and place on top of casserole. Bake 25 minutes at 400° in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Serves 8.

title: baby pearl tapioca
directions: Bring to a boil the water and salt.
Add tapioca.
Bring back to good boil again, cover and turn off heat.
Let set covered an hour or longer, until balls are clear.
Add Jell-O and sugar. Stir until dissolved.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add whipped cream and any fruit desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in next two ingredients. Pour into pastry shell and top with egg whites, beaten stiff.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese and onions.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.

title: pepper biscuits
directions: Mix 1/4 cup warm water with yeast and let stand about 1/2 minute before mixing in the flour.
Then add all ingredients, mix well and knead for about 10 minutes.
Make small rolls and let rise in warm place for about 4 hours.
Roll out small pieces of dough by hand into size of a cigarette and about 16 to 18 inches long, twist and make round circle's and brush with beaten egg. Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: party munchies
directions: Mix together oil, dill weed, lemon pepper and dressing.
Add crackers.
Put in large bowl; stir occasionally.
Store in airtight container.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut bread slices in half; cover bread with soup.
Roll up and take one piece of bacon and wrap around bread and stick together with toothpick.
Put on broiler pan and bake at 350° to 375° until bacon is cooked.

title: del's crab dip
directions: Very easy!
Just combine ingredients and serve surrounded by crackers.
Japanese rice crackers are the best.
I love this dip!

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread each tortilla with cheese; heat until melted.
In a bowl, toss chicken with salsa, peppers and onions.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into each tortilla.
Roll up tightly.
Makes 24.

title: mandarin duck salad
directions: In small skillet, melt margarine over medium-low heat.
Add almonds.
Cook until light golden brown, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 40 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles until tender.
Drain on paper towel. Brown meat; drain off excess grease.
Add spaghetti sauce and oregano.
Blend eggs and cottage cheese together.
Spread thin layer of meat mixture in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Layer of noodles, all of egg mixture, noodles, then rest of meat mixture.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: funnel cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Sift in flour, powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture through funnel into hot oil in skillet.
Cook until golden brown, turn carefully with tongs and/or spatula and cook one more minute.
Drain excess fat.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Serve hot with honey or syrup for dipping.

title: hash browns
directions: Layer 3/4 stick of margarine, hash browns, onion, sour cream and chicken soup (mixed together) and cheese.
Toss the corn flakes with 1 stick of margarine and use for top layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Empty boxes of sugar into large bowl. Mash out the lumps, then add milk and melted butter; mix well. Add coconut.
(May be easier to mix with hands.) Place in freezer for 1 hour, then roll into small balls. Put back in freezer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: square dance cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Pour
1/2 of batter in pan, then add 1/2 of topping, then remaining batter, then remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fish chowder
directions: In covered 5-quart Dutch oven, over medium heat, simmer potatoes, onions, celery, cloves, garlic, salt, bay leaf, dill seed and 1 cup water for about 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Discard cloves.
Add fish, 1 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Cover, simmer 5 to 10 minutes until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Garnish with parsley.

title: buffalo swingers wings
directions: Fry unbreaded Wingflingers according to directions.
Melt margarine and stir in remaining ingredients.
Coat cooked Wingflingers with sauce and bake 10 minutes in oven at 350°. Serve with Blue cheese dressing, celery sticks and carrot sticks.

title: tracey's vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth, potato and carrots in soup pot; bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients; cook on low for 15 minutes or until all ingredients are soft.

title: patsy's christmas cherry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese at room temperature until fluffy.
Add reserved juice from cherries.
Add remaining ingredients and fold together.
Chill in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in another pot.
Drain.
Put Cheez Whiz and melt.
Add soup and broccoli.
Put in dish and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 10.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook diced Chicken until tender, let cool for 1 hour.
Combine Chicken, Celery, Eggs, Onion, Relish, Mayonnaise, Salt and Pepper. Toss together.
Cut the tops off the Tomatoes, scoop out a portion of the pulp and discard; fill each tomato with a portion of the Chicken Salad and put each Tomato on a portion of the shredded Lettuce.
Chill for 1/2 hour in the refrigerator before serving.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix and drop on cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake until firm and brown.

title: dad's meat pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Layer in microwavable pie pan; soft shell, beans, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and picante sauce.
Layer again and cover with shell.
Microwave for 10 minutes or bake 10 minutes at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with more picante sauce; serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; remove from broth and cool.
Save broth.
Debone chicken.
Cook 12 to 16 ounces spaghetti in chicken broth until tender.
Do not drain.
When spaghetti is tender, add onion and green pepper which have been sauteed in butter.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and Velveeta cheese which have been cubed.
Add chicken. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in deep 3-quart casserole.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir well. Microwave again for 2 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, or until soft ball stage.
Add pecans and stir to coat.
Spread on wax paper and cool.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Put brown sugar, butter, half and half and salt into a 1-quart glass measuring pitcher.
Cook, uncovered, in a microwave oven 2 minutes at High, or until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Stir until blended.
Cook, uncovered, for 45 seconds at High, or until sauce comes to boiling.

title: mrs. logan's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter and sugar until light and smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fill sugar box with flour (to rim).
Add to above mixture and beat well.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Grease tube pan.
Add batter; shake down. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spaghetti with marinara sauce
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onion, carrots and garlic in hot oil until tender, but not brown. Add undrained tomatoes, sugar, salt, oregano, pepper and red pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes or to desired consistency.
Cook pasta in large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain well. Serve with tomato mixture. Serves 8.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Dry frankfurters and dip into combined ingredients.
Fry until golden brown.
Serves 10.

title: st. louis style peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter, sugar and
cream	cheese. Blend in 2/3 carton Cool Whip. Pour into pie
shell.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
Refrigerate for 2 hours until firm. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in a little salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and milk; stir in carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing and butter.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mix on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until heated.

title: hot crawfish dip
directions: Saute green onions in butter.
Stir in flour.
Add crawfish tails and fat; continue to saute.
Stir in mushrooms and seasoning.
Fold in sour cream just before serving.
Keep hot in chafing dish.
To freeze, omit sour cream and add when ready to serve.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 1 cup of sauce.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add egg, buttermilk and onion.
Mix well.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoons into deep hot grease (375°).
Cook, turning frequently, about 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: nell and maxine cheese spread
directions: Beat with
mixer.
Very good on rye bread.
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: crab souffle
directions: In 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan place 1/2 of cubed bread.
Mix crab, onion, mayonnaise, almonds, celery and green pepper.
Put over bread.
Put rest of bread on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt.
Cook until clear. Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease cookie sheets. Work butter in a bowl until creamy.
Add sugars and beat well.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Blend in water and peanut butter.
Gradually add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet, 2-inches apart. Crisscross with fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients well and stir in chocolate chips; leave in bowl.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Beat water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Combine with flour mixture.
Pour into greased and floured square or tube pan.
Spoon cheese mixture lightly on top, spreading with knife as you go. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sift confectioners sugar on top of cake.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add condensed milk.
Mix. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla; pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours. Top with cherry pie filling just before serving.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, butter and cheese.
Add salt, pepper sauce and Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls and flatten with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Bake on ungreased pan.
Makes a great snack.

title: white bread
directions: Put sugar, shortening and salt in a bowl.
Pour boiling water on top.
Stir to dissolve.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add 4 cups flour and beat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour gradually and mix to a dough that won't stick.
Knead lightly on floured surface 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; cover closely and let rise in a warm place until doubled, 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Punch down or knead 2 minutes to reduce to original size.
Let rise again until doubled, about 1 hour.
Knead down; divide in 4 portions and let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Mold in loaves; place in greased pans.
Cover loosely and set in warm place to double (about 1 hour).
Bake in a hot 400° to 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll out on well floured board and cut with your favorite cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on well-greased cookie sheet.
Yields 4 or 5 dozen.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break up saltines.
Mix all other ingredients except cracker meal.
Let stand until crackers are moist.
Add crabmeat; roll in cracker meal.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen medium crab cakes.
Let stand in refrigerator at least an hour before frying.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix margarine and cheese with a mixer.
Add remaining ingredients. Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet, flattened with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pannukakka(finnish pancake)
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch glass dish or 2 pie dishes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix soup and cream cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese is melted. Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Trim off thick part of each cabbage leaf.
Cover leaf with water; soak 2 minutes.
Mix beef, onion, rice, tomato juice and pepper.
Place about 3 tablespoons meat mixture on each cabbage leaf.
Tuck in sides and roll up.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Mix the buttermilk and soda and let stand. Beat egg whites until stiff. Cream sugar, oleo and shortening. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Add buttermilk alternately with flour to creamed mixture. Stir in vanilla. Fold in beaten egg whites. Gently stir in nuts and coconut. Bake in 3 or 4 layer pans at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; cool.
Beat eggs, salt and sugar. Add chocolate.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: mint candy
directions: Beat egg white until bubbly.
Blend in butter, sugar, flavoring and coloring.
This should be like cookie dough.
Knead well, then roll into balls.
Let sit on wax paper; press down with a fork.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook clams and bay leaf for 5 minutes with just enough water to cover.
Remove bay leaf.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter and add to clams and clam juice.
Add the thickened milk, potatoes and bacon bits; cook gently until potatoes are done.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic.

title: sugarless coffee cake
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Then, when cool, top with whipped topping.

title: yum yum pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, oleo and 1/2 cup
sugar.
Press 2/3 of this mix in large buttered casserole dish.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Stew chicken and cook pasta in broth.
Mix dressing, mayonnaise, cheese and olives.
Cut chicken into bite sized pieces and mix all together.
Store in tightly covered bowl.
Will keep up to two weeks.

title: chili
directions: Into a 2-quart pot, first add sauteed onion.
Brown and drain the meat; add to pot.
Then add tomato soup and chili powder. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans, stewed tomatoes, catsup and sugar.
Mix together and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: hunter-style chicken(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In large skillet, heat together butter and oil.
Cook chicken pieces over medium heat for about 25 minutes, turning to brown. Remove chicken to a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Keep warm. In same skillet, combine onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook and stir until onions are tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add wine, chicken broth and tomatoes; mix well.
Cook and stir over medium high heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Pour vegetable sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well. Add enough flour to make stiff easily handled dough.
Roll very thin
on floured surface.
Cut as desired.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or lightly brown.

title: grilled sausage and scallops with peppers, lemon, basil and garlic
directions: Blanch the scallops in boiling, salted water for 1 minute. Drain and allow to cool.
Cook the sausage in boiling water until completely cooked, about 5 minutes.
Drain and allow to cool. Thread the scallops, sausages and vegetables on skewers and season with salt and pepper.
Cook the skewers over a medium fire until all the ingredients have attained some brown crusting, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Slide the ingredients off skewers into a large bowl.
Add basil, garlic, oil, lemon juice and balsamic vinegar.
Shake the bowl until everything is well mixed.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sugar and then cold water and all juices.
Yields 60 (4-ounce) servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind in food grinder or blender the cranberries, apple and orange.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Combine all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Keeps well for days.

title: cold bean dip
directions: Start with beans and layer each item in a glass dish.
Serve cold.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, broccoli, onion and tomatoes.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, sauce and lemon juice; stir over vegetables.
Allow to set in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: power cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, sugar, butter and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and soda and beat into 1st mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and knead into first mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoons 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: lemon cream pudding
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in top of double boiler.
Add cold water and milk; blend until smooth.
Stir constantly over direct heat until mixture boils and becomes transparent-looking.
Place over boiling water, cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: cheezy cheese and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni for 2 minutes less than the box calls for. Drain.
Put under cold running water until macaroni is completely cool; drain.
In saucepan, place cut up chunks of Velveeta, butter, milk and flour.
Heat slowly, dissolving cheese and flour. Add all grated Cheddar cheese, except for 1/2 cup.
Pour over macaroni in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lentil stew
directions: In large kettle combine ham, onion soup, bay leaf, lentils, pepper, allspice, cloves, parsley flakes and salt. Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots, potatoes and celery. Return to boiling point, reduce heat, cover and simmer one hour or longer until ham and vegetables are fork-tender.

title: egg surprise pie
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Layer pie shell with cheese and sausage.
Pour egg mixture over this and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell.
Put on top crust.
Moisten bottom crust around edges to seal.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: summer vegetable pizza
directions: Other vegetables such as green peppers or onions may be used or included.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix all together except sour cream and croutons.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve with sour cream and croutons on top.
If you prefer, you can use tomato juice instead of the picante if you don't like it as spicy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together well.
Roll into ball or log shape.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate overnight to blend all flavors.
Serve with crackers.
Stays well in refrigerator several weeks.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs, cool and peel. Place eggs in jar, fill with remaining ingredients. Top with onions and fill jar with vinegar, seal, leave untouched for 24 hours.

title: cajun corn
directions: Cook onions in melted butter until tender. Add Ro-Tel. Simmer for 7 minutes. Add corn. Cook on low for 12 minutes. Add salt to taste.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: In skillet, cook sausage fully, then add onion until transparent. Drain well. Add to sausage mixture the next 7 ingredients; mix well. Chill for at least 2 hours. May do ahead and chill overnight. Then shape into small meatballs and roll in flour. Beat together milk and eggs. Dip meatballs into mixture, then roll in bread crumbs. Fry in oil until golden brown. Change oil when needed. Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grandma hillesland's "romme grod"(cream porridge)
directions: Bring cream to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes. Continue to boil while sifting flour into cream slowly, beating vigorously until mixture becomes heavy and butter starts to form.
Remove butterfat as it appears.
Add about 1 quart hot milk gradually and beat until smooth and the consistency of cooked cereal.
Add salt to taste.
Serve hot with butterfat, sugar and cinnamon.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together all the dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream the shortening and gradually add the sugar.
Continue to cream until light and fluffy.
Add and beat well the eggs.
Add alternately to the mixture the bananas and the flour mix.
Beat all until smooth.
Turn into a well-greased bread pan and bake for one hour at 350° or until bread is done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: spiced tea
directions: Tie spices loosely in bag and boil in water.
Add tea tied loosely in bag and steep 5 minutes; remove bags.
Heat frui juices and sugar; add to tea and serve.
Serves 25.

title: bean casserole
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice.
Layer 1 cup beans, 1/2 cup peas, 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice, 1/2 of the onion and 1/2 of the water chestnuts.
Spread 1/2 of the mayonnaise mixture and repeat.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serves 8 or more.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar together and spread on top. Cover all with cheese and chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 20.

title: glenda's 16 bean soup recipe
directions: Place beans in large kettle and cover with water.
Add salt to beans and water; soak overnight.
Next morning, drain and add 2 quarts water.
Add some ham or chicken pieces.
Boil slowly for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Add the rest of ingredients.
Simmer another 30 minutes and serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: chicken salad
directions: Poach chicken breast in water seasoned with black peppercorns, a little salt, celery tops and sprinkle of garlic salt.
Cook 5 minutes and turn off stove.
Allow chicken to sit in broth until completely cooled.
When the chicken is completely cooled remove from broth and cut into small dices.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mix chicken, celery, apples, walnuts, and sour cream/mayonnaise mixture well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours (or overnight).
Serve on butter croissants with leaf lettuce or serve alone with slices of fresh fruit in the summer for a cool evening meal.

title: party chicken sandwiches
directions: Blend all in an electric blender for about 1 minute.
Spread thin sandwiches with this and freeze or else freeze.
Spread in small amounts.

title: potato stuffing casserole
directions: In a medium skillet, saute celery and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add bread cubes and stir until lightly browned.
Stir in potatoes, parsley, salt, pepper, milk and egg. Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Garnish with additional parsley. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: trappers
directions: Bottom Layer:
Blend together cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and pecans.
Pat in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: beets - spiced
directions: Heat water, 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add beets.
Cover and heat to boiling; cook 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Cut beets into slices.
Mix olive oil, 1/4 cup vinegar, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, cloves and onions.
Pour over beets and marinate overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes in 9 x 13 baking pan. Mix with other ingredients. Top with 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Wash and peel peaches.
Drop peeled peaches into cold salt and vinegar solution (2 tablespoons salt and 2 tablespoons vinegar, 1 gallon water) immediately to prevent discoloration.
Mix sugar and vinegar and hot water; add spices (tied loosely in cloth bag). Boil and skim.
Wash peaches in cold water and drain.
Drop drained peaches into boiling syrup and cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Pack in preheated jars.
Cover with boiling spiced vinegar or let stand overnight in syrup, then pack in jars.
Cover with boiling vinegar.
Seal and process 30 minutes in hot water bath at simmering temperature.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in a cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes (as on package).
Let cool.
Mix the next four ingredients and spread on crust.
Chop all the vegetables fine and press on cream cheese mixture.
Next, press 1 cup shredded cheese on top of the vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry bread pudding(with almond cream sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine the bread with the 4 cups of liquid. Mix well. Beat together the eggs, sugar and almond flavoring. Combine with bread mixture and then stir in the cherries. Melt the butter in a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Pour bread pudding mixture into pan and bake for about an hour. Serve with Almond Cream Sauce.

title: cream candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and salt.
Cook until it forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla; set aside until lukewarm.
Beat until it thickens and is creamy.

title: chicken with eggplant
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Trim off eggplant ends, cut in 1/2 lengthwise and each 1/2 in thirds lengthwise.
Then cut across in 1-inch sections (total 5 cups). Cut onion in 1/2.
Slice thin (total 1 cup).
Core tomatoes and cut into small cubes (total 1 1/2 cups).

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Combine water and bouillon cubes in a heavy Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Melt margarine in heavy pan; blend in flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk and mix with a whisk. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring over low heat until melted.
Add all ingredients to Dutch oven, stirring over low heat.
Do not boil.
Serves 8.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, water and pineapple and boil gently together for 10 minutes.
Add cream cheese as soon as you remove boiling mixture from heat.
When cooled and beginning to thicken, add celery and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into ring or mold and chill thoroughly.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Toss; stir in dressing and chill.

title: swiss cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until smooth and of a spreading consistency.
Chill.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: mixed lobster and haddock
directions: Mix together all ingredients while fish is warm.
Place in refrigerator in a covered jar for at least 3 hours.
The haddock will absorb the juice and taste from the lobster.
Serve as a salad or lobster roll.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Grease a deep-dish pie pan and place a pie shell in bottom. Dump in all ingredients and mix.
Use the other pie shell as the cover, pressing the edges closed and trimming the excess.
Cut slits in top and bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Quarter biscuits and place in bottom of pan to cover.
Mix hamburger and sauce and then pour on top of biscuits.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Top with cheese and bake an extra 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm water.
In large mixing bowl, combine
salt,
sugar
and	shortening.
Pour
1/2 cup boiling water over this.
Add egg, then lukewarm water and yeast.
Add 3 cups flour and let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour). Knead down
on
floured
board.
Make
into
desired shape and allow to rise again about an hour.

title: preacher's pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked deep dish pie shell or 2 small shallow pie shells. Bake slowly in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until slightly set.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Cover and chill overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir on low flame sugar, water, butter and bananas (mashed) until butter melts.
Set aside to cool.
Beat eggs and vanilla; add to bananas.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to batter and stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased loaf tin.

title: stuffy noses
directions: Mix water and salt.
Place 1 or 2 drops in each nostril, then gently suction with bulb syringe.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream well the sugar and butter.
Add egg and pulp.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix all together. Add in raisins and nuts.
Mix. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with fried, crispy bacon.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise and spread over bacon.
Let set in refrigerator covered 2 hours or longer before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add and mix by hand the
shortening (oil), unbeaten eggs, vanilla and baking soda dissolved in buttermilk.
Add pecans and bananas.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or a large ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Roll into Italian bread crumbs until completely coated.
Place in baking pan.

title: cheerleaders cream cheese snack
directions: *The hot and spicy is particularly good.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
(Very good.)

title: lanette's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a casserole dish.

title: hot pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, mix the hot water and yeast.
Add water (warm) and sugar slowly.
Add 5 cups flour.
Stir until smooth (not sticking to sides); knead it.
Form dough into golf ball size balls and shape each into pretzels.
Fill a frying pan with water.
For each cup of water used, add 1 tablespoon baking soda.
Place pretzels in gently boiling water for 30 seconds.
Take out of the water and place on cookie sheet.
Salt pretzels.
Bake for 8 minutes until golden brown.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: crab critter fritters
directions: Remove	bone
from crab.
In mixing bowl beat egg, beer and stir
in Bisquick.	Add remaining ingredients, and gently stir
in crab.
In heavy skillet heat 2 or 3 inches oil.
Drop batter
into hot
oil (about 2 tablespoons for each fritter); fry
until golden
brown.
Drain
on paper towel.
Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: salmon with linguini
directions: In a large bowl, mix the linguini and Parmesan cheese.
In large skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Cook onion and garlic 1 minute.
Add peas, cooking an additional 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and mix with linguini. Toss in salmon.
Makes 6 servings less than 300 calories each.

title: cabbage beef casserole
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepan over high heat.
Cook ground beef and onions until pan juices evaporate and meat is well browned.
Stirring occasionally, remove Dutch oven from heat.
Add cabbage, carrots, pepper and 2 1/2 teaspoons salt; toss to mix well.

title: quick pound cake
directions: Add all ingredients in bowl. Beat for 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Spread on a cookie sheet 1/2-inch thick.
Chill several hours.
(Do not freeze.) Cut into squares and roll in flour.
Brown on both sides.
Put in a roasting pan. Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 cup water.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple crisp or paradise
directions: Slice the apples into a 7 x 7-inch pan.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with lemon juice.
With pastry blender, blend the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until crisp as desired.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill thoroughly.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Fold pudding and Dream Whip together.
Drain fruit cocktail and oranges.
Add to pudding mixture.
Mix in marshmallows.
Refrigerate.
Can add bananas at time of serving.

title: mazell's caramel icing
directions: Add 1 cup milk and 2 3/4 cups sugar in a large boiler.
Bring this to a rolling boil.
In a small skillet, caramelize 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour into milk and sugar mix.
Boil, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour into mixing bowl with margarine.
Beat well. (If too thick to spread easily, add milk 1 teaspoon at a time until right consistency.)
Spread evenly over cake layers.

title: black forest cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans.
Cool and remove.
Spread cherry pie filling between layers.
Layer plentifully on top layer.
Ice sides with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Boil carrots in salted water.
Cool.
Saute pepper and onion in small amount of oil.
Alternate carrots, pepper and onion in bowl.
Make a sauce of remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.

title: streusel-filled spice cake
directions: Stir together streusel ingredients until crumbly.
Cool. Prepare cake.

title: cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Heat.
Dissolve gelatins and cool.
Mix pineapple, cheese, nuts and cherries with gelatin.
Add cola last and blend.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan until firm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes.
Measure and add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook until firm.

title: blarney stones
directions: Heat sugar and eggs until like marshmallow consistency.
Add dry ingredients and boiling water alternately to sugar and egg mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 11 x 17 x 1-inch pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
After baking, let stand 10 minutes and turn out to cool.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and while still hot, stir well with wooden spoon.
Cool.
Form into small balls. Roll in granulated sugar.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together and put following dressing over all.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until top browns.

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish. Combine eggs, sugar and milk. Beat well. Fold in rice, lemon juice, vanilla, butter, nutmeg and raisins. Pour into casserole dish and put in pan of boiling water. Bake for 45 minutes or until custard is set. Bake at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and water.
Beat in eggs; add pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients twice.
Add 1/2 to batter, then add rest with nuts and the vanilla.
Grease four Number 303 cans with shortening; sprinkle with flour.
Fill cans 1/2 full; bake for 1 hour at 300°, or until done.
Remove from cans in 10 minutes.

title: sour cream deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Put yolks in small bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Fill the egg white halves with yolk mixture and top with sliced olives.

title: swiss fudge toffee
directions: Combine.
Boil for 20 minutes, stirring all the time.
Take off stove and add nuts, if desired, then beat well until it thickens.
Pour into a greased dish and cut in squares.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Prepare and bake care as directed.
While cake is in the oven, make the pudding as directed.
When the cake is done, poke holes all over it.
Then pour hot pudding over the hot cake.
Cool ten to fifteen minutes.
Then pour caramel topping over all this. Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Place ingredients in mixing bowl in order listed.
Mix slowly for 2 minutes.
Mix fast for 4 to 5 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak a la cheddar noodles
directions: Melt butter.
Add beef and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Saute until browned.
Remove meat from skillet.
Add onion and green pepper; saute 2 minutes.
Return to skillet with tomatoes and bouillon cube.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Add to meat mixture and cook until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook 2 minutes longer.
Prepare noodles and toss with grated cheese.
Serve meat over noodles.

title: baked salmon
directions: Combine margarine, bread crumbs and milk.
Bring to a boil. Stir in salmon, egg and salt.
Pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry or strawberry pretzel delight
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.

title: cinnamon almond cookies
directions: Beat at low speed 8 of the egg whites and granulated sugar for 4 minutes or until the sugar is dissolved.
Stir in ground almonds, cinnamon, flour, chocolate bits, lemon juice and cocoa.
Chill for 2 hours.
Put rounded teaspoonful of dough 1 inch apart on greased baking sheets.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cherries, sugar and jello.
Cook in saucepan until comes to a boil.
Let it cool and then add pineapple and nuts.
Stir well and refrigerate.
(May wish to use potato masher and mash cherries after cooking for better consistency.)

title: sacromonte omelette
directions: Cut up onions and pepper and fry until soft.
Add the pimentos. Mix well.
Add a pinch of salt to the eggs and beat well, then add 1/3 of the egg mixture to the pan, lifting the sides with a spatula so that the liquid covers the vegetables.
Add the remaining eggs. Wait until the egg mixture has set, that is, until the bottom is slightly toasted and the surface is still moist (not runny).
Put the spatula under the omelette and detach it gently from the pan. Add more butter (or oil) if necessary.
Slip the omelette back into the pan, this time undone side down.
Cook until this side has set.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass bowl, melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Combine with milk and sugar.
Cook for 4 minutes, stirring often.
Mix in margarine, vanilla and salt.
Beat with rotary beaters until smooth.
Serve over ice cream.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Drain and mash.
Spread potatoes evenly in a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sour cream. Sprinkle with bacon and green onions.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: scotch clusters
directions: Melt morsels in top of double boiler, stirring constantly. Break up noodles and pour into melted butterscotch. Add chopped nuts.
Using two spoons, spoon out clusters on waxed paper.
Do not have heat too high or morsels will harden.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use large cast iron skillet.
Put small amount of oil in bottom of pan.
Place in oven while you mix ingredients.
Mix cornbread according to package directions; add 1 can creamed corn.
When iron skillet is hot, remove from oven. Pour 1/2 mixture in bottom of pan.
Layer meat, onion, chilies and cheese.
Pour remaining batter on top to cover.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until brown and firm.
Cool slightly before cutting in pie wedges.
Great as a meal with a salad.

title: my cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Mix in the rest as listed.
Stir well. Drop on greased cookie sheet one teaspoon at a time.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 375°.
Do not half or double recipe.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Grease and flour a loaf pan.
In a large bowl, sift together the flour and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, cream together the butter and sugar, then beat in the egg and salt.
Alternately add the flour and orange juice to the creamed mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in the cranberries and pecans.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cranberry orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in large bowl. Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in orange.
Spoon into 5 cup mold.
Refrigerate about 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold; garnish as desired.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: seafood fancies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Separate dough into 12 pieces, then separate each piece into 3 equal layers.
Place on prepared cookie sheets.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease large iron skillet and heat. Lightly sprinkle with meat and let brown slightly. Pour half of batter in hot skillet. Sprinkle layer of cheese, then onion and then peppers. Pour remaining batter over contents. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: csorege (hungarian cookies)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Make a well in dry ingredients and pour in mixture of egg yolks, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend well.
Let dough rest for 1 to 2 minutes.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut dough into diamond-shaped pieces 2-inches wide at center and 6-inches long.
Make a 1-inch slice in center of each diamond; pull end through center, twisting slightly.
Heat oil to 365° and fry diamonds for about 3 minutes or until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together water, sugar and salt.
Add yeast to water.
Stir in egg and shortening.
Then add flour until you have soft dough. I add a little sugar to yeast water.
They are real good.

title: trifle pineapple dessert
directions: *To cut cake, cut into slices and then cube.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread using yellow cornmeal and chilies.
Cool. Crumble cornbread and bacon, then add the other ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
(May need additional mayonnaise.) Yield:
12 servings.

title: sweet potato sun wheels
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; peel and mash.
Beat potatoes until smooth.
Add egg, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Slice each pineapple ring to make 2 thin rings.
(Rings may break, but merely put together in a circle.
Also, it helps to freeze the pineapple before slicing.)
Place 8 thin rings of pineapple in a baking pan and place a mound of the potato mixture on each slice of pineapple.
Cover with the remaining 8 rings.
Bake at 325° until heated (about 30 minutes).
Remove and sprinkle with coconut. Place in oven to brown coconut or in broiler, watching carefully to avoid burning coconut.
Serves 8.

title: fat-free banana muffins
directions: Spray 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, using a wire whisk or fork, thoroughly mix sugar and orange juice.
Whisk in egg whites, corn syrup and orange peel until blended.
Gradually add to flour mixture, stirring until smooth. Stir in cranberries.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven 25 minutes or until lightly browned and firm to touch. Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Serve warm or cool completely on wire rack.
Store in airtight container.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, mustard, seasoned salt and pepper.
Toss with cabbage, carrot and onion.
Sprinkle with paprika or dill weed, if desired.
Makes 8 servings, 95 calories per serving.

title: drop nut cookies
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Beat the egg yolk and whites until thick.
Gradually beat in the brown sugar.
Mix in the nuts, oil, vanilla and flour until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes or until delicately browned.
Makes about 36 cookies.
Contains 40 calories per cookie.

title: diabetic pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add egg, milk and butter.
Mix well and measure 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Pour into a warm nonstick skillet until brown, turning once.
Makes 10 pancakes.

title: bananas foster(serves 4 people)
directions: You need a gas stove or stove top heated with gas or propane. Melt butter with brown sugar and place bananas around the sauce. Heat for about 2 minutes.
Pour creme de banana into the pan. Bring back to flame.
Repeat with brandy.
Pour sauce and bananas over ice cream.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly the oleo, shortening, 3 cups sugar and eggs. Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. May need to chill dough for a little while, then shape rounded teaspoonfuls into balls (whatever size you want your cookies). Then roll the balls of dough in the sugar and cinnamon mixture. Flatten a little and place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until set. Move immediately from baking sheet.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat white of egg until light and fluffy meringue forms.
Set aside.
Beat yolk of egg; add buttermilk, then dry ingredients and cooking oil.
Fold mixture into beaten egg white.
Pour batter onto hot griddle to form pancakes 4-inches in diameter.
Serve with butter, syrup or jelly.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until meat is browned.
Drain off fat, return to heat and add beans and tomatoes.
Cook for fifteen minutes.
Add cabbage, water, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cook for an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.
This stew is better served the next day.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water, oats and butter; let stand for 20 minutes. Add sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, eggs, flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, 50 minutes at 350°.

title: quick fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Coat oysters with mixture.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar and cream of tartar until stiff.
Fold in cracker crumbs, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and oleo.
The dough will be stiff.
Melt unwrapped caramels with other 1/3 cup milk until smooth.
Spread half of batter in rectangle baking pan with fingers in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle chocolate chips over baked batter and pour melted caramel over that layer.
Add nuts.
Drop remaining batter on this. It will look strange.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
No longer! Dough may not look done, but that's due to the melted caramels. Let it cool for a few minutes and then loosen around pan edges. Wait about an hour before cutting into squares.

title: beef casserole italiano
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.

Stir in the tomato sauce, parsley, oregano, basil, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, combine spinach, Ricotta cheese and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Spoon spinach mixture around edges of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour beef mixture into center.
Cut each Mozzarella slice into 3 strips and arrange in a lattice pattern over meat.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Melt margarine and add flour, salt and paprika.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk slowly.
Cook over medium heat and stir until sauce thickens and boils.
Put 1/2 of potatoes in greased casserole and add 1/2 of sauce.
Place slices of cheese on top.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 30 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: baked hawaiian chicken
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in ketchup, lemon juice, honey, soy sauce and ginger; stir until smooth.
Marinate chicken with above for at least 1 hour, better if overnight.

title: creamy peas and potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes and microwave on High (100% power) for 10 minutes or until fork-tender; set aside.
In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine the peas and water.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes or until peas are tender; set aside.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix with mixer all but shrimp.
Then add shrimp and stir in with spoon so shrimp stays whole.
Serve on crackers, chips or bread sticks.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Pour off any accumulated grease.
Add celery, peppers and onion; saute.
Add tomatoes and their juice.
Add remaining ingredients except for Cheddar cheese.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Place on heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Peel and dice onion; mix with potatoes.
Cut margarine into pieces and drop on top.
Add salt and pepper.
Fold over aluminum foil; roll edges to close.
Place over campfire or on grill for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn over every 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Beat together.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and flour.
Add butter, milk and 1/2 cup coconut.
Put 1/2 cup coconut on top of pies.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Yields two 9-inch pies.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add rest of ingredients except bread and mix well. Spray 11 x 13-inch baking dish (or pan) with Pam. Line with bread. Sprinkle raisins on top. Pour milk mixture over bread. Let set 30 minutes. Bake for 35 minutes at 375° or until done. Should shake like Jell-O when pan is gently shaken back and forth.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Steam the broccoli until tender. Chop coarsely and set aside. Saute the onion in butter or margarine until soft, but not brown. Add flour and stir until paste-like.
Blend in milk and cream. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Add cheese by the handful, stirring until smooth. Add broccoli and salt and pepper.
Serves 12.

title: easter cake
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes more, stirring continuously.
Add 1 capful vanilla.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle fresh coconut and place a few jelly beans on each piece of cake.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Mix sugar with flour and stir in beaten egg yolks and lemon juice/rind while gradually adding milk. Stir in butter. Set aside. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Place in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° until tests done. The top will have appearance of a cake with custard on the bottom.

title: potato soup
directions: In large kettle, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain, reserving liquid and setting vegetables aside.
In same kettle, saute onion until soft in margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved liquid from vegetables until soup is of desired consistency.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into squares and put in crock pot. Brown ground beef and add all ingredients and simmer on low until cheese is melted.

title: quick skillet stew
directions: Drain potatoes, reserving 1/3 cup liquid; slice.
In skillet, combine potatoes and reserved liquid with remaining ingredients. Heat; gently stir occasionally.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Discard tough parts and chop broccoli.
Add chopped onions, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise and pour over broccoli, mixing well.
Add bacon, crumbled, just before serving.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl cream together until fluffy shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Whisk in egg.
Stir in cocoa and milk.
Fold in flour and soda, mixed, and chocolate bits.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls onto nonstick (or greased) baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Cool about 5 minutes before removing cookies from sheets.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: overnight potatoes
directions: Boil and mash 8 potatoes.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, milk, egg and onion.
Dot 1/2 stick oleo on top.
Bake until brown at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can make 1 day ahead.
Refrigerate and then bake.

title: meatball hoagies
directions: Mix hamburg, bread crumbs and egg.
Add garlic salt, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Roll meatballs and add to own spaghetti sauce.
Cook on medium heat about 45 minutes.
When meatballs are done, add to buns.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese to top and bake in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with a side of spaghetti.

title: ham croissant appetizers
directions: Unroll dinner rolls.
Cut each one in half to form a small triangle.
Spread a little mustard on each triangle.
Place 1/2 teaspoon deviled ham and a small amount of cheese near the longest side of each triangle.
Roll up.

title: oatmeal cookies with dried cranberries and apricots
directions: Put rack in center of oven.
Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar with an electric mixer or food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and oats.
Mix until just combined.
Stir in cranberries and apricots.
Drop batter by tablespoon onto a prepared baking sheet, spacing cookies 2 1/2-inches apart.
(They spread considerably.) Bake until cookies are a medium brown, about 11 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Use metal spatula to transfer to wire rack to cool completely.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture. Fold in zucchini, coconut and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased and floured sheet pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise and add to broccoli.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place 1/2 cup crushed soda crackers on top and bake 15 more minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas on plate with a fork. Combine all ingredients, adding bananas last.
Mix well using a wooden spoon.
Place batter in greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 4-inch. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peaches 'n cream cake
directions: Mix cake and pour in cake pan.
Drain peaches and place on top of cake.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice and spread over top of peaches, to approximately 1 inch from edge of pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion; add salt.
Let this soak for 2 hours.
Place cucumbers and onions in containers for freezing. Dissolve sugar with vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers and onions just enough to cover.
Put in freezer.
When ready to use, remove and let thaw.

title: chicken-rice bake
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish (shallow), mix soup, water, rice, paprika and pepper. Place chicken on rice mixture. Sprinkle with additional paprika and pepper. Cover chicken and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Mix soup mixture with squash.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
In a 7 x 12 x 2-inch pan, layer 1/2 stuffing mix, then vegetable mix, top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread 2/3 of cornbread stuffing in bottom of 1 large baking dish, ungreased.
Sprinkle chopped chicken over mixture.
Mix soup, chicken broth, chopped celery, chopped onions and oleo together.
Cook this mixture in large boiler until onions and celery are tender.
Pour this over cornbread mix and chopped chicken.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until light brown.

title: mahogany cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar; add 1 egg at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour and baking soda and alternate with 1/2 cup milk.
Heat other 1/2 cup milk and chocolate.
Add while warm; beat well.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Use 10 x 10-inch pan.

title: cherry goodies
directions: *If using apple, add a little cinnamon.

title: crab cake casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except breadcrumbs and cheese in 1 1/2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with breadcrumbs and grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned and cheese has melted.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a hot, greased skillet or pan at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together margarine, sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla and baking powder.
After mixing all ingredients together, pour half of batter in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread 1 can of pie filling over batter.
Carefully spread remaining batter over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: In a saucepan, over medium heat, cook and stir butter and flour until smooth and bubbly, about 2 minutes.
Gradually add milk and lemon juice.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add celery salt, salt and pepper; mix well.
Remove from heat.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies in milk.
Take them out almost immediately and layer in bowl with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: hearty fiesta burgers
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, crumbs, taco sauce, onion and salt. Add ground beef and mix well. Shape mixture into 6 patties. Brown on both sides. Mix soup, chili beans and peppers (if desired) and pour on top of patties. Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes. Top with shredded cheese. Melt cheese and serve.

title: strawberry-nut dessert
directions: Bring 1 cup water to boil.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved. Add juice from frozen strawberries and pineapple.
Chill until thickened but not set.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream oleo, Crisco, white and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add peanut butter.
Drop by tablespoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into tube pan sprayed with Pam and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix
together to make a dough, not too thin and not too thick. Roll
out
on
floured surface and cut out with cookie cutter. Bake at 375°.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy
bars
over	low heat with 2 cups evaporated milk. Mix eggs and sugar in large bowl and beat well.
Mix in melted candy bars and milk mixture.
Pour into freezer can and finish filling
with
milk
to
within 2 inches of top of can. Freeze until ready.

title: dumplings
directions: Put flour, Crisco and salt in mixing bowl until it resembles corn meal.
Add milk and egg. Roll out on floured board and cut into strips.

title: make ahead breakfast bake
directions: Crumble sausage in medium skillet; cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well. Spread bread cubes in a buttered 12x8x2 in. dish.
Top with sausage and cheese. In a separate bowl combine eggs, milk and seasonings. Beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Mix in egg and buttermilk.
Mix together oats, flour, baking powder, salt and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in bananas.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: delicious cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook pineapple and sugar together for 5 minutes.
When cake is done, poke holes all over it and pour pineapple mixture over top while both are still hot.
Let cool.
Make pudding and pour over cooled cake.
Put in refrigerator to cool set.
Then spread whipped cream over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add eggs and oil (do not beat).
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and the banana.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.

title: cream of rice pudding
directions: The CoCo Lope and Harina de Arroz can be bought at Foodtown, by the Goya products.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and pour into 2 greased loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Remove from pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: pronto potato soup
directions: In small frying pan, brown bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Add onion to drippings in pan and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain fat off.
Meanwhile, in 3-quart saucepan, mix cold potatoes and soup until smooth.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, to desired consistency over medium heat.
Add bacon and onions.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Lightly grease bottom of pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in greased loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Mash bananas and combine with water.
Add bananas and sifted ingredients alternately to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fried pies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add Milnot to which egg has been added.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Roll out thin on lightly floured board and cut circles.
Place between wax paper.
These can be made ahead of time.
If they are wrapped, they will not dry out.

title: rhubarb pie for 1
directions: Wash, clean and cut rhubarb into bite size pieces (enough to fill 9-inch pie pan).

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool and drizzle with glaze.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl, stirring until moistened.
Knead dough 20 times on floured surface.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with round biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Mix lukewarm water and yeast; set aside.
Mix together oil, salt, sugar and 1 cup water; then add yeast.
Add flour.
Make into a dough ball; coat bowl and top of dough ball with oil.
Cover with a tea towel and put in a warm place, or in sink with warm water. Let rise about 1 or 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Let rise again about 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in size.
Make rolls.
Let them rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
If you like a soft crust, coat baked rolls with butter and cover with tea towel for 5 minutes.
To make sweet rolls, add more sugar.

title: apricot delight
directions: Heat apricot nectar just under boiling point.
Add jello and sugar; let cool.
Add frozen orange juice, crushed pineapple, nuts, banana and marshmallows.
Stir in salt and lemon juice. Congeal in refrigerator.
Optional:
Serve with thin layer of Cool Whip.

title: apple bean bake
directions: Cook apples in melted butter until tender.
Add sugars.
Cook until sugars melt.
Add last four ingredients; stir together well. Combine with beans.
Mix well!
Pour all into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 400° about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin orange-pineapple salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle gelatin over mixture; stir well.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Combine pecans and coconut.
