Sprinkle over salad.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Makes 15 servings.

title: blueberry pecan delight
directions: Mix all together and congeal.

title: french rolls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add beaten eggs.
Liquefy yeast in 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add to mixture.
Add milk and enough flour to make stiff, smooth dough.
Let rise 5 hours.
Take off large chunk off dough; roll thin on floured surface.
Cut into wedges, spread with soft butter.
Roll from broad end to narrow end.
Place rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise 3 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 60 rolls.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix the ingredients all together except vanilla.
Cook over medium heat for 1/2 hour, stirring constantly, or until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add the vanilla and beat by hand for 1 minute.
Then pour into a buttered pan.
Cut into inch squares.

title: parmesan dip
directions: Melt cream cheese and milk in a double boiler.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle on top green onions and paprika.
Serve with sliced French bread.

title: elephant stew
directions: Onion odor will cling to many containers, especially plastic, but is easy to remove.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Heat iron skillet or heavy baking pan with a little oil. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon meal and brown lightly.
Then add batter and bake at 400° until browned on top, usually 20 minutes or so.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, raisins, nuts and candied fruit.
Heat milk; add marshmallows and heat until melted.
Add butter and water; mix thoroughly.
Pour over graham cracker mixture and mix. Line pan with waxed paper.
Press mixture into pan.
Cover with waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 3 days before cutting.

title: country steak
directions: Pound steak.
Cut into serving size pieces.
In skillet, brown steak in oil.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Stir often.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gourmet cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Peel and shred.
In saucepan, combine butter and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Fold into potatoes.
Pour into a greased baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut
the squash and onion.
Boil
until
tender.
Drain and mash.
Add
salt,	pepper, eggs, soup,
butter
and
1/2 cracker crumbs;
mix well.	Layer 1/2 of the squash mixture in a dish. Sprinkle this with 1 cup of cheese.
Spread remaining squash
on top of cheese and sprinkle	the
remaining	cracker crumbs on squash.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top of the crackers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato dish
directions: Combine sweet potatoes with 1/2 cup pineapple, salt, butter and honey or brown sugar.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg and garnish with remaining crushed pineapple. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, peppers and onion.
Sprinkle with turmeric. Dissolve salt in 2 quarts cold water and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.
Cover vegetables with cold water and let stand 1 hour.
Drain thoroughly.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling and pour over vegetables.
Cover and let stand 12 to 18 hours in a cool place. Simmer until vegetables are hot.
Bring to boiling.
Pack boiling hot into hot jars, leaving 1/8-inch headspace.
Adjust caps. Process 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: blueberry cake or muffins
directions: At low speed cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs (1 at a time).
Mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mash 1/2 cup blueberries; stir in by hand.
Fold in rest of blueberries.
Pour in greased tube pan or muffin tins.
Sprinkle with sugar on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: granny's italian cookies
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco until very creamy.
Add eggs and beat very well.
Add vanilla.
Put flour, baking powder and salt through sifter and mix thoroughly into batter; should not be sticky.
Grease cookie sheets.
Drop by teaspoon onto sheets and form with fingers.
Bake at 400° until cookies are light brown. Ice with powdered sugar and milk frosting.

title: shepherd's-cheese pie
directions: Brown your meat; drain your meat.
Saute onions and bell peppers with butter.
Add to the meat.
Add season and sauce to meat.
In your oblong casserole dish, spread meat evenly on bottom of dish.
Spread creamed potatoes evenly over meat topped with shredded cheese.
Place in oven at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strata
directions: Line a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan with 10 slices of bread, then ham, cheese, bread (10 slices), ham and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, onion salt and mustard; pour on top of bread, ham and cheese.
Cover; let stand overnight.
Take out 10 minutes. Uncover; bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Take out of oven; let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean thoroughly and boil for 5 minutes 10 large mushrooms. Remove stems and boil as well.
Saute onion.
Add mushroom stems. When these are cooked add Parmesan, parsley and garlic.
Fill mushrooms.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Drain
orange
segments and set aside.
Combine gelatin and water,
stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add sherbet and mix well. Add
orange segments and stir until well blended.
Pour into lightly oiled mold and refrigerate.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until brown.
Add onions and saute for a few minutes.
Add brown sugar and vinegar, then chopped potatoes. Turn down heat and allow to season through.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 medium loaves.

title: appetizer meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except cranberry sauce, and tomato sauce.
Shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Brown on all sides.
Remove from pan into a deeper pot, draining off extra fat. Combine cranberry sauce with tomato sauce.
Pour over meat balls. Cover and simmer over low heat about 45 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish.
Provide toothpicks.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in Cheez Whiz until melted.
Spoon into oblong casserole dish. Prepare cornbread mix as directed.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Spoon over meat and cheese mixture. Bake at 375° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: pizza snack
directions: Put 1 tablespoon sauce on each tortilla slice.
Sprinkle about 1 teaspoon of cheese onto each slice.
Put slices on a tray and put in toaster oven or oven for 3 to 5 minutes on 350°.
In microwave, only cook 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: classic spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach until dry.
Stir together all ingredients. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve with bread, crackers, vegetables or chips.

title: alpine goulash with buttered noodles
directions: Brown meat well on all sides in hot drippings or shortening. Turn cubes to brown equally.
Add balance of ingredients, cover and cook slowly until beef cubes are tender, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: hominy grits casserole
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add hominy and cook 3 minutes.
Beat eggs in a cup and finish filling with milk.
Stir in egg mixture, butter and garlic cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Use a large bowl.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over the shredded wheat and let stand. Cream sugar, shortening and eggs, well beaten.
Add shredded wheat mixture and other ingredients.
Let stand 36 hours before using.
Fill muffin tins slightly over half and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Batter keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Beat together cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk.
Spread on crust.
Spread pie filling over filling and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, and baking soda.
Then add 1 egg, beaten with juice of the fruit cocktail.
Add medium can of Fruit Cocktail.

title: easy cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to boil in medium saucepan, separating broccoli with fork.
Stir in Velveeta cheese.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in Minute rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt; stir in cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk and Wesson oil.
Beat with rotary or electric beater until just smooth.
(Do not overbeat).
Pour into greased iron skillet or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fred's favorite raisin custard pie
directions: Cook raisins, sugar, 1 1/2 cups water and vinegar about 10 minutes.
Mix egg yolks, remaining water, cornstarch and butter. Add to raisins and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Serve with whipped topping.

title: low-sugar - low-fat delight
directions: Make jello with 1 3/4 cups boiling water.
When cool, add yogurt.
Whisk to mix.
Refrigerate.

title: drop donuts
directions: Stir with fork and drop by teaspoon into hot grease for about 3 minutes.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Mix together oil, dressing and dill weed.
Pour over crackers in a Ziploc bag.
Shake.

title: bev's super squash
directions: Wash zucchini and cut in 1-inch slices.
Put in a large pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 5 minutes only.
Drain squash very well.
Cut scallions into very small pieces (use the green and white part).
Put the squash into a long baking dish, sprinkle scallions on top of squash.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Slice cheese and place on top.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted, about 15 to 25 minutes.

title: favorite chocolate cake
directions: Beat together sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Gradually add the 1/2 cup sour milk and 1 cup boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Grease and flour pans lightly.
Frost with your desired frosting.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 layers, bake 25 minutes.
With one 9 x 13-inch pan, bake 45 minutes; 30 cupcakes, bake 25 minutes.

title: crab and shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple 'n' honey scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray large cookie sheet or grease lightly.
Combine first 7 ingredients; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add apple, milk and honey, mixing until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface; knead gently 5 to 6 times.
Pat dough into a 9-inch circle.

title: christmas snack mix
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients all together in large pan. Over this pour the remaining ingredients. Cook 2 or 3 hours in oven at 250°, stirring very 15 or 20 minutes until crisp. Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: cherry mountain ice cream pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into the crust.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Crumble pecan cookies over ice cream to form second layer.
Place cherries over cookie layer.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine spaghetti, chicken, olives, onion, seasoning and broth.
Bake until hot.
Add sour cream and stir.
Place almonds on top and heat through.
Serve with French bread and a salad.
A great way to use leftover chicken or turkey.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour pan. Beat butter and cream cheese together in bowl until well blended. Add sugar to mixture and cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition. Add vanilla and lemon flavor. Sift flour and blend into creamed mixture. Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bacon monkey bread
directions: Combine bacon, Parmesan cheese and onion; set aside.
Cut biscuits into fourths; dip each piece in butter.
Layer one third in a 10-inch lightly greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle half of bacon mixture over biscuits.
Repeat procedure, ending with biscuits. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Invert onto a serving platter.
Serve immediately.

title: grandmom's yum yum cake
directions: Cook the first 7 ingredients slowly for approximately 15 minutes or until raisins are puffy.
Set aside to cool, then add soda.
Set aside until cold.
Add flour and water last.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in Bundt pan.
Do it right and it's yummy!

title: no peek chicken
directions: Put rice and water in dish and mix.
Layer remaining ingredients and bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jerusalem artichokes with cream sauce
directions: Wash and peel the artichokes, slice in covered pan.
Cook in small amount of water (salted).
Boil for 10 to 15 minutes until tender.
Drain well.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and white pepper; add cream or milk, all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in parsley.
Serve sauce over cooked artichokes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: frozen cranberry cups
directions: In food processor or blender, combine berries, sugar and pineapple until
finely chopped.

title: macaroni goulash
directions: Cook macaroni firm as directed.
Brown turkey and onion together in 4-quart pot.
Drain.
Add stewed tomatoes, oregano, garlic, ketchup and salt.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add macaroni and simmer 10 minutes more.
Serve with salad.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Add nuts and stir.
Bake in small

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Slice cucumbers and onions.
Soak in salt solution (2 quarts water and 1/2 cup canning salt) for 3 hours.
Mix vinegar, sugar and spices; bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions, just to heat thoroughly (until cucumbers change colors).
Pack hot cucumbers into jars, leaving 1/3 inch space.
Cover with boiling hot liquid.
Adjust lids and seal.

title: peachy fruit salad
directions: Puree first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Place remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Pour peach sauce over fruit.
Toss until covered.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cranberry sauce.
Chill until syrupy.
Add nuts and celery.
Stir in sour cream.
Chill at least 4 hours in a mold.

title: vegetable burgers(serves 4)
directions: Will need aluminum foil squares.

title: london broil marinade(serves 6)
directions: Mix ingredients together to blend.
Pour over 2 pound cut of London broil.
Marinate 3 hours or overnight.
Broil over grill or in the oven.
For medium rare, broil about 15 minutes on each side in the oven.

If you are cooking on the outdoor grill, adjust the time according to the distance your rack is from the coals, 15 minutes on the first side and 10 minutes on the other side might produce the desired doneness.
Slice diagonally, very thin. Serves 6.
(The amount of marinade is enough for a large cut of steak.)

title: belgian waffles
directions: In medium bowl, combine first four ingredients.
In separate bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Add the liquid into the dry ingredients. Beat until smooth. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in Belgian waffle maker.

title: spicy shrimp etouffee(ay-too-fay)
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter; add garlic powder and celery seed.
In a bowl, combine cornstarch, red and black pepper, 1/4 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir into cooked vegetables. Add tomato sauce.
Stir in shrimp.
Bring to a boil; then reduce heat and simmer briefly, just until heated through.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Toss chicken with olive oil, oregano and salt. Cook in skillet over medium heat until done. Add onions and heat through. Heat pita bread in microwave. Spread pita with sour cream and chicken mixture. Top with lettuce, tomatoes and cucumber. Fold and enjoy.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 2-inch balls and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: doughnuts
directions: Shape or cut a hole in center.
Cook in hot oil (skillet). Shake in a brown paper bag filled with sugar. Eat while warm.

title: kid's barbecue chicken
directions: Place mixture of half cornmeal/half flour with salt/pepper to season in paper bag.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then drop in paper bag; shake.
Pan-fry until golden brown and done through.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until beef is lightly brown and onion is tender; drain off fat. Stir in salsa, taco seasoning and water; cook over low heat 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture thickens. Stir in corn and olives. Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Layer in 10-inch pie plate.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix melted butter, flour, 1 cup sugar, egg and chopped pecans.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix well and pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel apples and slice. Add remaining ingredients. Mix with apples and let stand while making crust.

title: california pie
directions: Fold in crumbs and nuts to first 3 ingredients.
Butter pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool; top with Cool Whip, ice cream or whipped cream.
I like it served without topping.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 12 glass pan 20 minutes at 350°. Cool slightly.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat
eggs
with electric mixer.
Add sugar while beating. Other
ingredients
should be added in the order listed, beating well after each addition.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add enough
milk to fill container.
Freeze in ice cream freezer according to directions.

title: red pepper round steak
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Cut strips into 2-inch pieces.
Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces and pour mixture of ingredients over pieces.

title: mexican chili bake
directions: In large skillet, cook onions, green peppers and garlic in butter until tender but not brown. Stir in rice, tomatoes and seasoning.
Heat thoroughly.
Saute beef; stir beef into rice mixture.
Spoon half of beef-rice mixture into buttered, shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup corn chips.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until heated thoroughly.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Let cabbage, green pepper and carrots set 1 hour.
In saucepan, add vinegar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar. Bring to a boil.
Pour this over cabbage, green pepper and carrots.
Let set 2 hours.
Drain well and place in freezer containers and put into freezer.
When ready to use, thaw and mix in mayonnaise to taste.

title: taco crescent pie
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add taco mix, water and olives. Simmer 5 minutes. Separate rolls and put in ungreased 9 x 10-inch pie plate to make crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup crushed chips over bottom crust. Spoon on meat mixture, the sour cream, cheese and top with remaining corn chips.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Slice and serve. Top individual servings with as much lettuce, tomato and taco sauce as desired.
Freezes well.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill.

title: lotsa layers salad
directions: Twenty-four hours prior to eating, make in order by layering lettuce, celery, green pepper, water chestnuts, onions and peas in a bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread with spatula over top.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown on top.
Place casserole in pan of water to prevent burning. Serves 4 to 5.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until
it	thickens, stirring to prevent lumping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and set aside to cool.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add milk and eggs.
Beat well. Stir in vinegar and vanilla. Add butter and nuts. Pour into pie crust and place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sis haack's black-eyed peas(beans)
directions: Fry until cooked the oleo and hamburger.
Add the other ingredients and let simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Add a little water, if dry.

title: eggplant pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and blend.
Then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
For mellowing of flavors, cover and store overnight.
Do not use cake mix that has pudding added.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in microwave for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, pepper and garlic.
Microwave for 10 minutes.

title: melt aways cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients and add flour, nuts and coconut.
Form balls using a teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll or sift with powdered sugar.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add milk; mix well.
Add oleo, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch glass pie pan which has been lightly greased.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crust.

title: hungarian pastry
directions: Mix well by hand until no more yellow or white shows.
Flatten out, wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: cabbage vinegar salad
directions: Chop and blend together all vegetables and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix and boil remaining ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Soften leaves in boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix together all remaining ingredients, then shape into small roll and roll up in cabbage leaves.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Place in greased baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle rice in pan. Place chicken breasts on rice.
Mix canned soup
with water; pour over chicken and rice (lift chicken enough to allow liquid to reach rice underneath).
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken and rice.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours, or until chicken is done (juices run clear when poked with fork).

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in oblong dish 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nan's lime delight salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions and let chill until it begins to thicken.
When thickened, take out of refrigerator.
Add the cabbage, carrots and pineapple.
Return to refrigerator to jell until served.

title: tater crisp chicken
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Rinse fryer in cold water and cut into serving pieces.
Pat dry.
Dip pieces in melted margarine and roll in potato flakes.
Place skin side up in prepared dish and season to taste.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Blend with milk, sugar, lime juice and cornstarch.
Whip over hot water until slightly thick.
Put into baked pie shell.
Top with favorite meringue recipe.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Beat the eggs in a bowl.
In separate bowl, add chopped onion, soup, mayonnaise and beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add cooked, drained cauliflower to the first mixture; mix thoroughly.
Mix melted butter and bread crumbs together; sprinkle over cauliflower mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peppered rib eye steaks(dry marinade)
directions: Brush steaks with olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine all seasonings.
Sprinkle seasoning over steaks and press into both sides.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.
Grill steaks.
We have used this on every cut of steak, even deer steaks, and it is very good.

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Discard hot pepper.
Pack into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Cover with metal lids.
Screw bans tight.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yield:
11 half pints.

title: southern italy meat balls
directions: Add all ingredients; make 6 meat balls.
Saute in olive oil until brown; drain and place meat balls in gravy.

title: spanish pie, potato
directions: Cube the potatoes in very small
cubes.
Put them in frying pan with
2 tablespoons butter (melted).
Let them fry while stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Cut slivers of green onions in very little pieces.
Get a casserole bowl and preheat oven to 350°.

Butter bottom and edges of bowl; take the slightly cooked potatoes and cover bottom of casserole dish, then mix green onions, grated cheese, 1/2 pound grated ham and put a layer of this mixture on first layer of potatoes.
Repeat with putting final layer of potatoes on top.
Beat 2 eggs and pour over top of whole mix and let eggs run through whole mixture.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes approximately.
This is sooo good you'll want to slap the cook, but don't, because he or she has feelings, too.
I picked this recipe up in Spain.

title: ginger pickles
directions: Peel and cut cucumbers in small strips.
Soak 24 hours (2 gallons water and 3 cups lime).
Rinse well.
Soak 2 hours in alum and water to cover them.
Wash 3 times.
Soak 6 hours in ginger and water to cover.
Rinse well.
Drain.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel onion and slice thinly. Melt butter slowly in pan.
Add onion and cook slowly over low heat, stirring often, until onion is golden brown. Add 6 cups water and the bouillon cubes.
Cook at least 1 hour. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when served.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix Sure-Jell with strawberries in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Add sugar and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Seal in jars and let cool.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Blend the ingredients into a ball and serve with a variety of crackers.

title: meal-in-a-dish
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Place in casserole dish.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with grated cheese return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: barbecued cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat for about 1 hour, or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Work first four ingredients like a pie crust (leave crumbly). Put 2/3 into a 9 x 13-inch pan and press down lightly.
Slice apples on top.
(If keeping apples very close you will need 7 or 8 to fill pan evenly.)
Mix the last 3 ingredients in a dish; add this mixture and cover the entire apple pan.
Add the remaining pie crust on top to cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Check on apple softness; different apples take a longer period of time for baking.)

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream together shortening and lemon extract, add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients 2 times.
Add liquids and dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture, beating only until smooth after each addition.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze as dry as possible.
Mix with yogurt cheese, egg whites, onion, 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese and spices. Cook pasta according to package directions.
Stuff shells or manicotti with spinach mixture.
Put in 11 x 14-inch casserole dish sprayed with nonstick baking spray.
Cover with sauce, which has been diluted with water.

title: chocolate brownie deluxe
directions: (Perry County Fair 2nd Place Hershey's Greatest Cocoa Cookie, Brownie, Bar Contest.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut 12 doughnuts and holes from bread.
Remove crust from scraps, fitting scraps in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place cheese slices in layer over bread, followed by a layer of broccoli, then a layer of ham.
Arrange bread doughnuts and holes on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours, or overnight.
Bake uncovered in slow 325° oven for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle some grated cheese over top 5 minutes before end of baking.
Serves 12.

title: garry's rum cream pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks until light in color, then gradually beat in the sugar.
Soak the gelatin in the cold water and put on low heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
In a slow stream, pour the gelatin mixture into the egg mixture, beating constantly.
Cool mixture.
Stir in the rum.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cook and stir beef until brown; drain.
Put in taco seasoning.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion and put aside.
Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Pat into greased pan; press to 1/2 inch on sides of pan.
Layer beef, tomatoes and then green peppers in pan over dough.
Spoon sour cream mixture over top.
Bake until edges of dough are light brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef wellington
directions: Preheat oven to 425°
Place meat in lightly greased roasting pan. Sprinkle with pepper if desired. Roast at 425°
for 30 minutes or until thermometer reads 130°.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill first if possible. Pour in 4-quart freezer, then add sweet milk if not full to freezer line.

title: tomatoes provencale
directions: Halve tomatoes and place on cookie sheet.
Crumb toast.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the crumbs.
Pile mixture on tomatoes and broil 5 to 7 minutes.

title: grilled steak and vegetable salad
directions: Grill steak over medium-hot coals to desired degree of doneness, about 20 minutes for medium, turning halfway through cooking time.
Slice steak, diagonally across grain, into scant 1/4-inch slices.
Combine sliced meat and vegetables in shallow serving bowl.
Pour dressing over and toss.
Serve immediately or refrigerate several hours.
Serve chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated sweet and sour salad
directions: Cook carrots, in boiling salted water to cover, in a large saucepan, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain; cool. Combine carrots, onion and green pepper in a serving bowl.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan mix brown sugar, shortening and butter.
Cook and stir over low heat until butter and shortening melt.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop from teaspoon 3 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° about 7 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix thoroughly first 7 ingredients.
Turn over lightly with hands.
Put in cleaned crab shells.
Top with cracker crumbs. Next, spoon melted butter over cracker crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until browned.

title: chicken cheese soup
directions: Cover vegetables with water and simmer until tender.
Bring the bouillon cubes and 2 quarts of water to boil, being sure that the bouillon cubes are dissolved.
Melt butter in another pan; add flour to butter slowly.
Stir constantly.
In just a few seconds, it will be thick.
Then add to this mixture, stirring quickly, 1 cup of the boiling water with bouillon cubes, then add a little more, then add all of this mixture to the water mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Add this mixture to the vegetable mixture.
Do not drain vegetables.
Add Cheez Whiz to soup and stir until dissolved. Add peas to soup.
Add chicken cubes.
Add bacon crumbles.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
You're done.

title: stuffed chicken
directions: Pound each chicken breast into long thin pieces.
Place 1 piece of ham and cheese on each chicken breast.
Fold chicken breast in half.
Garlic salt each side of chicken.
Place chicken in hot pan with a small amount of oil.
Cook chicken until done, turning often (medium high heat; 20 minutes).

title: applesauce doughnuts
directions: Blend butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Mix applesauce and soda and add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Roll out and cut.
Fry in deep fat (350° to 375°).
Drain.
May coat with granulated sugar or powdered sugar.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased skillet or pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt in large bowl, and mix well.
Combine butter and cocoa; stir into egg mixture. Add pecans and coconut, mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until set.
Yields:
1 pie.

title: romaine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle into unbaked pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs and combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell containing sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes on rack.

title: shipwreck
directions: Use 2 1/2-quart dish, brown ground beef slightly.
Layer potatoes, ground beef, onions, kidney beans, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste and pour tomato soup over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: bread pudding(makes 6 servings)
directions: Scald milk with butter.
Stir in all other ingredients, except the eggs.
Mix well, then add eggs last, stirring gently.
Pour into greased pan.
Place pan in hot water and bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve about 1 ounce butter sauce with each serving.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Using a shortening cutter, cut margarine into flour until it is in coarse cornmeal sized granules.
Add water 1 to 2 tablespoons at a time.
Just enough to bind the dough together. Overlap 2 sheets of plastic wrap (14-inches long with 2-inch overlap).
Very lightly sprinkle them with flour.
Put half dough on wrap.
Sprinkle dough ball with flour, and put 1 more sheet of plastic wrap on top of ball.
Roll thin.
Remove half of plastic wrap and lay crust in pan.
Do not remove top sheet until dough is shaped in pan.
This way the dough doesn't stick and there isn't a mess.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: crab quiche
directions: Melt butter.
Add green onions and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Mix eggs, cream, milk and salt.
Stir in green onion mixture and remaining ingredients.
Divide between 2 pie crusts and bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Then reduce heat to 325° and bake 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, line the bottom with the tortillas, then layer the chicken pieces, onion and the remaining liquid mixture combined with the seasoning.
Cover with cheese and bake in a moderate oven for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Blend in 1/4 cup light brown sugar until smooth.
Place in shallow dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: quickie fruit dip
directions: Mix together with a mixer until smooth. Serve with your choice of fruit.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken wings in a single layer in shortening in electric skillet set at 300°.
Remove as they brown; drain drippings.
Add vinegar, sugar, pineapple juice, catsup, soy sauce, mustard and salt.
Bring to a boil at 250° for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chicken wings.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Turn wings over and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes more.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook onion and bacon together in the microwave for about 2 minutes in a microwaveable dish.
Add pork and beans and brown sugar.
Mix together well.
Place back in microwave.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Stir beans and cook for another 10 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over Chex in large bowl.
Put powdered sugar in large grocery bag.
Pour in mix and shake well.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan with wax paper.
Grease and flour.
Set aside.
Beat eggs in a large bowl at high speed until thick.
Gradually add sugar and beat 5 additional minutes. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Gradually stir into pumpkin mixture.
Spread batter evenly in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup pecans, gently pressing into batter.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Sift flour and combine with next 4 ingredients. Combine egg, buttermilk and margarine; add to dry mixture. Stir until smooth. Stir in banana. Use 1/4 cup batter for each pancake. Pour onto hot griddle coated with cooking spray. Turn only once when edges look done. Serve with maple syrup and strawberry preserves.

title: crown jewel patties
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add bread crumbs.
Shape into patties and coat with corn flakes.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° until brown.

title: summer relish for cold meats
directions: Mix well all ingredients and chill.

title: heavenly turtle pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, nuts and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and begins to pull away from sides of pan, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Spread nut mixture in bottom of baked pie shell.

title: cheesy baked fish
directions: Bake fish until almost done.
In the last 5 to 10 minutes of baking, lay cheese across fish, then cover with picante sauce. Return to oven.
It is ready as soon as cheese melts.
This is good with any mild flavored fish.

title: strawberry stuff
directions: This is a layer dessert.
Tear cake into small pieces (about 1-inch cubes).
You want to smash up strawberries and have plenty of juice.
I usually add a good cup of sugar to the strawberries while they are thawing.
Spoon strawberries and juice over cake. This juice will soak into the cake, then spoon some Cool Whip over the top of the strawberries.
First layer is cake, second is strawberries and third is Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Cool Whip should be on top.
I usually make 6 layers.
It is usually colorful in a glass dish.
This is easy and tastes really good.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: They seem not to firm until chilled. No extra flour.
Mix oil, melted chocolate and sugar in a bowl. Beat in eggs one at a time. Add vanilla and dry ingredients and chocolate chips. Chill several hours.
Roll into balls and top with powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with buttered stuffing mix or Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's vegetable soup
directions: Add ingredients to a crock-pot and cook all day.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place 1/2 teaspoon dill seed in bottom of pint jar, approximately 4 pints.
Wash okra and pack as tightly as possible in jars, being careful not to bruise.
Add 1/2 teaspoon dill seed, 1 pod red and green peppers and 1 clove garlic to each jar.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil. Pour hot mixture over okra; seal and allow to stand 2 weeks.
Serve icy cold.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a roaster and smooth it out. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mrs. field's cookies(makes 112.  can be halved.)
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and chocolate bar.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: deluxe potato bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, bread crumbs, onion, milk, seasoned pepper and seasoned salt.
Drain potatoes and stir in egg mixture.
Add 1/2 of Cheddar cheese and 1/2 bacon.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bacon.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Garnish with additional cooked bacon and parsley.

title: hamburger barbecue sandwiches
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, green pepper and onion, stirring to break up meat into small pieces.
When meat is brown and vegetables are tender, pour off excess drippings.
Mix vinegar, mustard, ketchup, sugar, Worcestershire and pepper; add to beef mixture.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Shape into balls or crescent shapes, about 1/2 tablespoon in size.
Bake 15 minutes. Cool. Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Grind fruit including peels of lemon and oranges.
Cook in a large roaster pan in a 300° oven for 2 hours.
(Cook, uncovered.) Stir every 20 minutes.

title: miracle whip salad dressing cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add salad dressing; mix well.
Add vanilla and water; mix well.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lorie's pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into small cakes.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Spread on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black and white brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine brownie mix, water, oil and egg.
Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Add 1 1/2 cups pecans, chocolate chips and coarsely chopped baking bar; mix well.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 33 to 39 minutes or until center is set.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with finely chopped baking bar.
Let stand 2 minutes to soften; spread evenly over brownies.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Mix in order.
Mix well and chill for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop squash and onion and boil together until tender.
Remove from heat and drain, then stir in salt, pepper, milk, butter and egg; mix well.
Crush crackers.
Grate cheese, then pour into 2 layers.
Start with squash, then cheese and crackers.
Repeat again.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream margarine and Crisco. Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs separately.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: molasses surprise cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add eggs; mix well. Sift together flour, salt, soda, ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add small amount of dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Stir in sour milk, nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix in remaining dry ingredients.
Drop from tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple walnut bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix sugar, crumbs, peanut butter, and butter until well blended.
Scrape into a 9x13 inch ungreased pan; press into an even layer.
Spread melted chocolate over top.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 15 to 20 minutes before cutting bars.

title: pineapple snow
directions: Mix all together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: casserole supreme
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well. Add onion, chili powder, Heinz 57, tomato juice and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 20 minutes. Combine pork and beans, ketchup, sugar and mustard; add to meat mixture. Grease a 2-quart casserole; alternate layers of meat mixture and spaghetti. Cover with enough additional tomato juice to completely cover top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Shred cheese.
Crumble crackers until fine in a blender or use rolling pin.
Layer macaroni, cheese and about 5 slices of margarine twice.
Add milk about halfway up in bowl.
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs and pepper (optional).
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown or 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and form into bite size balls and chill.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip each piece with a toothpick and place on waxed paper to dry.

title: potatoes hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger, then add onion and peppers.
Cook for 10 minutes, then add potatoes, sliced with skin left on.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange and pineapple chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir 3 minutes. Drain.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in combined dressing, juice and sugar. Add rice and green pepper. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add oranges and pineapple chunks.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour peach pie filling in large bowl with lid.
Drain all other fruit and add pineapple last.
Stir and let stand overnight. Stir before serving.
Good with any meal.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Bake in hot oven 45 to 60 minutes. When done, cut crisscross on top and scoop out potato; mash.
Add milk, margarine and seasoning.
Refill potato shells and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: lane cake
directions: Bake mix as directed on box.
Let cool, split the layers once and set aside.
Cook together the yolks, butter and sugar until thick; add the rest of ingredients and cook until it thickens again.
Lay the first split layer on serving plate and spread the cooked ingredients over each layer.
Do not put it on sides until you are finished and you know there is enough left over to do them.
This cake is pretty if it doesn't have it on the sides. Also, you can place cherry halves on top of cake.

title: cavitini
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding cooked and drained noodles and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into balls the size of a quarter.
Bake on a foil-lined cookie sheet at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth. Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn the mixture into the pan. Spoon the pie filling into the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each directions.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden.
Filling will sink into the cake while baking.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift the flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add water and milk all at once and mix just until dough follows fork around bowl.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter, glass or cup.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes, just until golden brown on top.
Yields
16 medium biscuits.

title: farmers meal
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Cook, peel and shred potatoes. Place hamburger, potatoes and soup in layers and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Put cheese on top when nearly done.

title: cabbage lasagna
directions: Saute ground turkey, onion, and green pepper until meat is browned.
Boil cabbage until tender.
Save 2 cups liquid and drain off excess.
Combine 2 cups liquid, oregano, pepper, salt, and tomato paste and simmer on low heat for 4 minutes.
Add meat, onion, and pepper to mixture.
In a 9x13 pan pour half of meat mixture, then add cabbage, Pour remaining meat mixture and then top with shredded mozzarella.
Bake at 400 until cheese is browned, about 30-45 minutes.

title: grecian shrimp
directions: Saute onion, lemon juice, oregano, butter in oil.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Before serving, add feta cheese in large chunks into hot mixture.
Serve hot over pasta or rice or serve cold on romaine lettuce.

title: b.b.  king's beale street blues sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves. Serve warm.
Refrigerate unused sauce for up to several weeks.

title: cool carrots
directions: Peel carrots.
Cook until tender. Slice into pennies.
Saute onion and pepper in small amount of oil until just tender.
Add salt to cooking water.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar. Heat to dissolve sugar.
Add other ingredients and pour over carrots. Cover and refrigerate at least overnight.

title: shrimp curry
directions: In microwave oven, simmer butter, onion and celery until soft in a 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Add all other ingredients. Cook on simmer until shrimp are pink, approximately 15 minutes. Some microwaves vary.

title: slaw
directions: Shred the cabbage, onion and pepper.
Pour 1/2 cup sugar over the top.
Do not stir.
In a saucepan, combine the oil, vinegar, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Bring to a boil and then pour over the cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Do not stir. Refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: vegetable soup (italian style)(very unusual soup)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in olive oil.
Add broth, tomatoes and rice.
Simmer longer if using wild rice. Add zucchini, potato and beans.
Add water as desired.
Serve with grated Mozzarella or Parmesan cheese.

title: turkey salad burritos(serves 4)
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine turkey, celery, black olives and cheese.
In another bowl, whisk together salad dressing, picante sauce and salt.
Pour sauce over turkey mixture.
Blend well.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Pour spices over meat and marinate for 15 minutes.
Broil over a low flame for 10 minutes on each side.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Slice cake in thin pieces. Arrange 1/2 of cake pieces in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Beat the cream cheese and sugar. Beat in Cool Whip.
Spread half of the cream cheese mixture over the cake. Layer more cake slices on top.
Spread remaining cheese mixture over cake layer. Top with cherry topping.
Chill.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; finely chop stems.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat.
Add mushroom stems and onion.
Cook, stirring, until onion is limp.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, crab, bread crumbs, egg, dill and 1/4 cup cheese.
Blend well.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar together well and put into greased 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over rhubarb. Finally, mix last three items together.
Crumble and add on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Reserve 1 egg for garnish.
Chop other 2 eggs; lightly toss together chopped eggs, beans, celery, relish, onions and salt to taste.
Gently blend in sour cream.
Cover and chill to blend flavors.
Serve garnished with egg; 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese may be added before the sour cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up the chicken as you would for frying.
Brown slightly in small amount of oil and set aside.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, place a layer of sliced potatoes and then cover with a layer of peas.
Arrange pieces of chicken over this.
Add salt and pepper to cream and pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and return to oven until chicken is brown. Add biscuits for topping if desired and bake 15 minutes or until chicken and/or biscuits are brown.

title: red-fruit punch
directions: Mix all together in a gallon container.
Finish filling with water and place in freezer.
Take out morning of the day of serving.

title: baked corn
directions: Stir eggs.
Add flour and all the other ingredients; mix well. Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side. Do not cook longer or they will be overcooked and dry.
Transfer to warm serving platter.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter/oleo with the sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until top is nice and brown, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Brown onion in melted oleo.
Place pork chops in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle browned onion over.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until pork chops are done.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and cook to a rolling boil. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop on wax paper.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Add lemon juice, sugar, butter and marshmallows to slightly beaten eggs.
Cook until dissolved, then cool to room temperature. Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Grease and flour pans, 5 mini or 2 large loaf pans.
Toast coconut in shallow baking pan in 350° oven for 7 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Set aside.
Mix together cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil.
Mix for 1 minute.
Add poppy seed and coconut.
Pour into pans.
Bake in 350° oven.
Five mini loaf pans, bake about 30 minutes.
Two large loaf pans, bake about 45 to 60 minutes.
Done when knife comes out clean.

title: baked ham
directions: Stud ham with cloves.
In a blender, combine the next four ingredients and pour over ham.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, reduce heat to 300° and bake for 2 hours.
As the pan juice cooks down, add ginger ale.
Baste ham every 15 minutes, adding ginger ale as needed.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Make paste of flour, sugar, salt and juice.
Add butter.
Cook until thick.
Add egg.
Cool.
Add juice of 1/2 lemon.
Chop pineapple, oranges, marshmallows, cherries and nuts.
Add cooked dressing and whipping cream.
Fold all together.
Freeze.

title: seven can casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna pie
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter for 10 minutes.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Add soup, salt and pepper; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Take off heat; stir in drained tuna.
Chop eggs; stir in.
Pour into small greased casserole; top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: texas straw hats
directions: Brown ground beef in one skillet and drain.
Meanwhile, saute onions, pepper and celery in 3 tablespoons cooking oil just until onions are clear and celery is still crisp.
Combine browned beef with sauteed veggies in a large pot.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over Fritos and top with grated cheese.
Serves 6 + as main dish or many more when used as a "Dip" for holiday parties!
Learned this one when I was a girl scout.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine 1 cup oleo, powdered sugar and eggs. Beat with electric mixer for 15 minutes. While this is mixing, combine 1/2 cup oleo and the graham cracker crumbs. Pat this mixture real firm into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the filling on top. Slice the bananas over the top of this.
Sprinkle the pineapple over this. Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate 3 hours. Cut in squares and serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in deep dish.
Add all the other ingredients over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove cover and bake 1/2 hour or until brown and chicken is done.

title: new potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes; leave the peeling on.
Slice potatoes in about 1/8-inch pieces.
Cook in boiling water until done.
Drain water and pour potatoes into bowl.
Chop bacon and onion and put in bowl with potatoes.
Pour Ranch dressing over mixture and toss.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna cheese souffle sandwich
directions: Place 4 slices bread in greased 8-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients, except soup and eggs.
Spread evenly over bread in pan.
Blend together soup and eggs, pour over sandwiches.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set and lightly browned.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir together sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs and pumpkin.
Add and mix in dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: healthy oven-fry chicken (tenders or breast)
directions: Coat chicken lightly with melted margarine and dredge in seasoned dry bread crumbs.
Place in an ungreased shallow baking pan.
Oven fry at 425° for 5 to 9 minutes on each side until golden brown and cooked through.
For crisper chicken, coat pan with 1 tablespoon melted margarine or vegetable oil and preheat oven for 5 minutes before adding chicken.

title: cookies
directions: You first put some sugar in, then flour and beat 'em.
Then you put in a last thing is to cook it.
Then you eat it.

title: cheese ball
directions: Whip up cream cheese with fork until creamy.
Put in all ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Mix and form in ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Wrap in aluminum foil and let set overnight (so flavors will not be so strong).
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Slice eggs over. Dilute soup with 1/2 can chicken broth.
Pour over above.
Spread dressing mix over this.
Pour 1 1/2 cups broth over dressing mix. Put pats of butter on top and sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cold taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with sour cream (with electric mixer).
Add taco seasoning and mix.
Pour in dish.
Drain salsa sauce well and sprinkle over mixture.
Place shredded lettuce on top, then fresh tomato and then shredded cheese.
Serve cold with taco chips. Serves 10.

title: weight watchers breakfast muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into muffin pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in butter.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Arrange in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and zucchini.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon, sifted together.
Add zucchini mixture, blending well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except ground beef.
Mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly. Place in loaf pan and bake 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel potatoes and slice.
Boil in salted water until tender. Drain potatoes.
Mash thoroughly and add eggs.
Mix well.
Add sugar and butter and milk and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake on 350° until done.
This mixture will be soupy.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: For crust, mix cake mix, coconut, butter and 1 egg until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 9x13 inch pan.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: open face tuna sandwiches
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in order (tuna on toast, with the onion over tuna and the eggs over onion).
Mix the soup, milk, parsley and lemon juice together.
Pour over sandwiches and broil 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: eggplant casserole(wonderful!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover peeled and diced eggplant with water; add 1 teaspoon salt and simmer over low heat until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside to cool.
Combine eggplant with remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into square or round baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Recipe makes 6 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: barbecue kielbasa
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened, stirring occasionally. Yields 4 servings.

title: browned rice no. 2
directions: Cut up
onion
and
celery.
Brown in butter.
Add rice and brown.
Place in casserole; add salt, pepper, consomme and water. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: red lobster cheese biscuits
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients to a soft dough. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Melt the last 3 ingredients. Brush mixture over biscuits immediately out of the oven!

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: Pound steak 1/4-inch thick; cut into serving pieces.
Blend egg and milk.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Slowly brown meat in hot oil, turning once.
Cover; cook on low heat for 45 to 60 minutes, until tender.
Season to taste.
Serves 6.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Beat margarine and Crisco until creamy.
Add sugar gradually; beat well.
Add milk slowly, beating until light and fluffy.

title: rhubarb preserves with jello
directions: Cook rhubarb until done.
Add sugar and Sweet*10.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour this mixture over jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Put in jars.
Enjoy the preserves!

title: three layer strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven 7 minutes; cool.

title: moo-moo good
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Add tomatoes, beans and rice.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed Fritos and grated cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Put milk, onion, lemon juice, Tabasco, celery salt, garlic salt, salt, pepper, and egg in a bowl. Add salmon that has been boned and dark skin removed. Flake with a fork. Add oleo and crumbs. If dry, add salmon juice. Pour into a buttered casserole dish and bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Serves 4-6.

title: velvet salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-o, pineapple and sour cream. Mix cool whip, nuts, and marshmallows. Combine Jell-o mixture with cool
whip mixture. Chill in mold or bowl for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil for 4 minutes.
Combine chicken and vegetables; stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise and soy sauce to taste.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix
together rice, chicken, broccoli, cream of chicken soup, water,
salt,
pepper
and poultry seasoning.
Top this with dabs of butter.	Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Drizzle melted butter over
the	crumbs.
Bake
at
350° until top is brown.

title: mexican hero
directions: Toast Chex crumbs in a 300° oven for 10 minutes; set aside. Combine egg, seasoned salt and taco sauce.
Stir in ground beef and Chex.
Shape into 4 oval patties to fit bread loaf.
Broil or grill for 10 to 12 minutes, or until done.
Turn midway.
Place, end to end, on split French bread.
Spoon on additional taco sauce.
Top with tomato, lettuce and cheese.
To serve, place top on loaf and slice crosswise.

title: sweet and sour mustard
directions: Mix mustard and peppers with enough water to make a smooth paste.
Add sugars and vinegar.
Bring to a boil, stirring continuously.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Add a little of the hot mixture to the eggs; mix well. Pour this into hot mixture in pan.
Continue to stir.
Bring to a boil again over medium heat.
Pour into jar.
Cool and refrigerate. This is guaranteed to open your sinuses!!!

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Brush one side of one slice bread with melted butter.
Spread Russian dressing on other side of bread slice.
Place corned beef on dressing, put sauerkraut on top of corned beef and then the cheese on top of that.
Cover with other bread slice.
In a skillet, melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter; place sandwich in skillet and cook until browned and cheese is melted.
Serves 1.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Put each vegetable through food chopper, using coarse blade. If vegetables are covered with liquid, drain off and discard liquid.
Measure each vegetable after chopping.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake in
moderate
oven
for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs gently with sugar.
Add oil, water and pumpkin.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 loaf pans.

title: slaw salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Set aside.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage immediately; mix well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: acorn squash
directions: Bake squash in oven or microwave until nearly tender. Saute apple and celery in butter for 5 minutes. Stir in crumbs and salt and pepper. Fill squash with mixture and top with cheese. Bake 15 minutes longer until tender. Serves 2.

title: philadelphia relish
directions: Let stand at least an hour before serving.
Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix soup, butter and Cheez Whiz in saucepan until melted and smooth.
Add hominy and onion.
Put crushed Fritos on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no ball sugar cookies
directions: With mixer, mix sugars, oleo and oil, then beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add them to mixture.
Cover and place in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in hot pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Melt oleo.
Add powdered sugar and creamy peanut butter; mix well.
To this mixture, add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.

title: snicker cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Roll into balls the size of a quarter and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Place sausage in iron skillet and bake at 500° until done.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook box of macaroni.
Combine soup and milk in a saucepan. Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Grease bottom and sides of a deep Corningware dish.
Layer with cooked macaroni.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces and layer; then add a layer of soup mixture and finally a layer of grated cheese.
Continue layers, ending with a layer of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly around edges. This is great reheated in the microwave!

title: banana split salad
directions: Drain pineapple reserving 1/2 cup of juice.
Set aside.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: wild plum jelly
directions: In a large kettle, simmer plums and water until tender, about 30 minutes.
Pour through a damp jelly bag, allowing juice to drip into a bowl.
Measure 5 1/2 cups of juice; return to the kettle. Add pectin; stir and bring to a boil.
Add sugar; bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim off any foam.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process for 5 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yield: about 8 half pints.

title: maque choux
directions: Saute onion for a few minutes in olive oil and butter, then add bell pepper.
A couple of minutes later, add corn, stirring all the while.
This mixture should just be about done, then add diced tomatoes.
Cook about 2 more minutes, then season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wiener and potato casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix in next 4 ingredients.
Add both milks. Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute or until thick.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Boil potatoes and cut in cubes; place in casserole dish.
Cut up wieners and add to potatoes; mix in sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream together oleo, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle top with a little sugar and cinnamon.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Melt shortening in skillet; add beef, onion, salt, pepper and flour.
Cook until meat loses its red color, stirring occasionally.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in water, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup; simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes or until of desired consistency.
Serve in buns.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Blend softened margarine and grated cheese. Add flour, salt and cayenne pepper. Knead dough, finally adding Rice Krispies. Roll in small balls, then flatten with hand on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until done, approximately 10 to 12 minutes, depending on the oven.

title: rob's fried zucchini
directions: Combine egg, milk, flour, salt and garlic salt in bowl; mix well to form batter.
Dip each zucchini round into batter; fry in deep fat.
Batter zucchini when ready to fry so each piece is coated.
Fry until crisp and golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: no bake peanut cookies
directions: Cook hard the sugar, milk and margarine for 1 1/2 minutes. Add the oats and peanut butter.
Stir thoroughly and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, peppers, carrots and salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Boil sugar, vinegar and celery seed for 3 minutes.
Let cool. Pour over cabbage mixture.
Pur into containers and freeze.
To serve, simply thaw.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip, then add fruit cocktail and jello.
Let set for 2 hours before serving.
Keeps in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: spinach salad
directions: Place all ingredients in blender except for oil and poppy seed.
Process for 15 seconds in blender.
Then add oil and seed. Mix well.
Serve with salad of spinach, mushrooms, bean sprouts, mandarin orange, small red onion, fresh strawberries and sunflower seeds.

title: aloha cake
directions: Follow directions on mixing from the back of cake box.
Use the pineapple juice in place of water.
If pineapple juice is not enough just add water for the right amount required.
Cook cake by using directions from cake box.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk (that's required on pudding box).
Add sugar to taste. Next, spread whip topping.
Then place cherries for the finishing touch.
Add pecans if desired.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: mostaccioli and sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage; drain.
In 2-quart baking dish, combine sausage, sauce, noodles and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Mix well.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and line cake pan with mixture.
Beat egg whites, butter and powdered sugar for 10 minutes and spread over cracker mixture.
Add pineapple, slice bananas long ways and place over pineapple.
Top with whipped cream, nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: erin's heavenly salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Stir in sour cream thoroughly.
Add marshmallows.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt
the chocolate and peanut butter. Add all ingredients and mix
well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool and place in a tin.
Keeps well.

title: coconut-cranberry chews
directions: Beat the butter, sugar, orange peel, and vanilla until smooth. Beat in the egg. Mix in the flour, baking powder, and salt. Mix until dough comes together. Mix in the cranberries and coconut. Shape into balls and place on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 350 for 10-15 minutes. Let cookies cool... and then enjoy!

title: lo-cal summer dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.
Yield: 2 1/4 cups.

title: easy chicken breasts
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken. Stir well. Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good with rice or mashed potatoes. Makes lots of gravy.

title: cranberry cherry pie
directions: Let pie crust stand out of refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and blend.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough, about 1 inch apart, on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until very light brown, at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: our lord's old scripture cake
directions: Beat on low speed until pecky and fluffy.

title: whiskey balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in blender, also nuts and coconut.
Mix all together, form in balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: venison lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Brown meat and onion in oil. Drain.
Add oregano and sauce to meat.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Layer noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese in pan.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Mix vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer until well blended, then cool.
Pour over vegetables.
It will stay crisp for several days.

title: super macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients and chill at least 4 hours.
(Can use yellow or red bell peppers.
Some of each looks pretty.)

title: champagne strawberries
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar in bowl.
Stir in white wine. Chill several hours.
Spoon sauce and strawberries into four 6 ounce goblets.
Pour champagne over each.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Mix thoroughly until moist. Pour into two greased bread pans.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Mix until crumbly and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Chill slightly and mix again.
Fold in whipped topping and chill overnight.

title: caramel apple slices(microwave)
directions: Melt caramels with water in microwave bowl, stirring occasionally.
When ready, spoon over apple slices.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 egg and butter.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine remaining eggs, sugar and cream cheese together, mixing well.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheesy chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Use water from chicken for soup. Shred the chicken, add other ingredients and enough water to cover everything good.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: flan
directions: Blend eggs and milk for 2 minutes.
Heat sugar in pan over very low heat until caramelized.
Immediately put caramel into large container, add remaining ingredients on top of caramel. Cover container and place into a larger pan filled with water. Heat over medium-low heat until ready.

title: french onion bread
directions: Soften yeast in the warm water.
In a large bowl, combine shortening and hot water.
Add the sugar, salt and soup mix and stir well.
Add yeast mixture.
Gradually add the flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on a floured board until smooth and elastic. Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again 1/2 hour.
Shape in 2 loaves; it makes nice round ones in 8-inch cake pans.
Let rise until light and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
In layers on top of hamburger, put cheese, chopped chilies and onion. Pour on cream of mushroom soup and put on Tater Tots in rows. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and store in an airtight container for up to 6 months.

title: tuna goulash
directions: Mix in baking dish and pour 1 can mushroom soup over top. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mrs. ruth's cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in 1 cup hot water.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350°.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Fry hamburger and drain.
Mix together hamburger, sauce, chilies, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine spaghetti and sauce; mix well.
Layer two 9 x 13-inch baking dishes with half the spaghetti; top with half of the cheese and cover with remaining spaghetti and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(Half recipe fills one 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: wacky cake
directions: Add all dry ingredients into sifter.
Sift right into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make 2 small "holes" in pan.
In one hole, add oil, the second hole, vinegar, then pour cold water over everything.
Mix with fork until flour is wet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: speedy chili
directions: Melt fat; add hamburg, onion and pepper.
Cook until meat is lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add kidney beans, chili and salt.
Simmer.

title: peppermint kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff enough to hold in points.
Add 8 tablespoons of sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Fold in remaining sugar, salt, candy and chocolate bits.
Cover cookie sheet with unglazed paper and drop mixture by spoonfuls onto sheet. Bake at 275° for 30 to 35 minutes, until delicately browned, firm and dry.
Remove from paper immediatley.
Kisses should be used within one week after baking, unless frozen.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and cranberries together and let stand overnight or several hours.
Add gelatin to boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add other ingredients and chill.
Use the pineapple juice and less water if desired.

title: beef n' bean pie
