directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, half of the dry bread crumbs, 1/4 cup cream of mushroom soup, egg, thyme leaves, salt and pepper.
Press mixture evenly against bottom and sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Cover meat mixture with the French-style green beans.
Spread remaining cream of mushroom soup over the green beans.
Bake uncovered for approximately 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: kentucky biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine with pastry blender until mixture resemble coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk.
Mix quickly to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead a few times to make a soft dough; don't overknead or the biscuits will turn hard and dry.
Roll out to a 6 x 6-inch square.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
With knife, cut dough into 12 even portions; do not separate.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
Dust with flour and melted butter.

title: one rise monkey bread
directions: Grease a 12-cup fluted tube pan or 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, blend 1 1/2 cup flour, sugar, salt, yeast, water, margarine and egg at low speed until moistened.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour by hand.
Knead dough on floured surface until smooth about 1 minute.
Press and roll dough to 15 x 2-inch rectangle.
Using sharp knife, cut dough into diamond shaped pieces by cutting into 2-inch strips diagonally across dough.
In shallow pan melt the 1/3 cup margarine, dip each piece of dough in melted butter and place in prepared pan, making layers.
Sprinkle each with poppy seed.
Cover.
Let raise in a warm place until light and double in size (45 to 60 minutes).
Heat oven at 375°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, deep brown.
Butter top while still warm.

title: jello plum pudding
directions: Dissolve gelatin dessert mix in boiling water.
Stir in cold water and spices.
Chill until very thick.
Fold in the remaining ingredients and chill until firm.
Good with hard sauce or whipped cream.

title: butter fingers
directions: Sift about 1/2 box confectioners sugar; measure out 4 tablespoons sugar.
Cream butter and sugar; add flour and pecans. Make out in finger size rolls.
Cook in slow oven, about 250° or 300°, until brown.
Roll on remainder of sugar.

title: hero hamburgers
directions: Combine beef and 1/4 of barbecue sauce, eggs and salt.
Mix lightly and divide into 16 portions.
Gently shape into thin round patties.
Place 1 teaspoon each:
barbecue sauce, cheese, relish and onions on 8 of the patties.
Top them with remaining 8 patties.
Press edges together; broil or fry 4 minutes on one side, turn, baste with remaining barbecue sauce and cook 4 minutes longer or until meat is done.
Serve on buns.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dad's own barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil on medium high in a medium saucepan until soft (about 5 minutes). Add the garlic and saute for a minute more.
Transfer the onions and garlic to a medium bowl.
Add the ketchup, mustard, honey, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, molasses, cinnamon, salt and cayenne pepper and mix well.
Pour over or brush on meat during last 3 or 4 minutes of barbecuing.
The sauce is best for chicken, ribs or pork chops.
If you don't like this, you don't like barbecue.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix egg
yolks	with
milk.
Mix
cornstarch with brown sugar and
add
egg
and	milk
mixture
gradually.
Add salt. Cook, stirring
constantly
until
thickened.
Add butter and vanilla. Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and
beat until stiff peaks.
Pour filling in baked pie shell. Top
with
meringue and bake at 400° until browned on top.	Cool and chill.

title: frozen berry-melon pops
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender. Cover and blend until smooth. Press fruit mixture through a fine mesh strainer over a bowl to extract juices. Discard solids. Pour mixture into 3-ounce paper or plastic drink cups or pop molds. Cover with foil. Cut a slit in the foil and insert wooden sticks. Freeze several hours until pops are firm.

title: spicy chicken with olives
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Crush garlic under flat blade of chef's knife; remove and discard peels.
Set aside.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Cool completely. Do not work with it if it is warm.
Add oleo and shortening.
Beat until creamy and frost.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Slice each tray of rolls through the middle.
Spread sauce on both halves of each tray.
Place ham on bottom halves.
Top with remaining halves.
Cover trays with foil.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Best served hot.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, white sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the milk, oil and vanilla until smooth.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 9 square baking pan. Combine brown sugar and remaining cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over all.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream if desired.

title: osceola cheese dip
directions: Mix all but garnish and then top around edges or center of spread with them.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes, but check off and on.
Serve with favorite cracker.

title: holiday ham and chili cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheeses, deviled ham, scallions and chilies; mix well.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill.
Remove from refrigerator to soften slightly before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers. Makes 1 (2-cup) cheese ball.

title: snow caps
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise.
Place in shallow pan.
Combine onions and potatoes.
Put on top of hot dogs.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves four.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix in 9 x 13-inch greased pan with egg, 1 cup cheese, milk and garlic salt.
Pour spaghetti sauce over spaghetti.
Add 3 cups cheese and arrange pepperoni on top. Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: old fashioned apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese, pepper, salt, mushrooms and onion in a bowl.
Gradually add milk.
Stir in potatoes.
Place in a greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with remaining cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl. Add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add egg yolk, flour and cinnamon; mix until well blended. Press mixture into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Pour egg white over surface; drain off excess. Sprinkle chopped pecans over top. Press lightly into dough. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into 3 x 1-inch bars; cool on wire racks. Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: *Brandy, rum or sherry to taste may be used in place of vanilla.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Heat tomato juice and sugar almost to a boil.
Dissolve flour in milk; mix to a thin paste and add to tomato juice.
Stir until smooth and thick, cooking thoroughly.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add water.
Stir until shiny.
Add milk. Mix well.
Pour in deep pie shell.
Dot with butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate and set aside.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except crab meat with mixer, then add crab meat and mix with a spoon.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in Pam sprayed pan.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top and return to oven to melt.

title: cherry something
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Mix with Cool Whip and nuts.
You can use a serving dish or individual dishes.
Place angel food cake on the bottom of dish.
Put pudding mixture on top of cake.
Pour cherry pie filling over this and refrigerate.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well in blender.
Serve as a fresh dip for vegetables.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Use 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: rhubarb pudding cake
directions: Slice rhubarb into 1-inch lengths.
Arrange in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Cream the shortening and 3/4 cup of sugar. Blend in bran flakes.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk to shortening and sugar mixture.
Spread batter over rhubarb.

title: spaetzels(chewy european dumplings)
directions: Mix to a stiff smooth dough.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon into boiling water, dipping the spoon into water between each dumpling to keep dough from sticking.
Boil about 5 minutes; drain.
Serve with goulash and stew.

title: hot or mulled cider
directions: Heat well, but do not boil.
Serve warm.

title: smoky salmon dip
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 2 tablespoons salmon liquid.
Flake salmon and set aside.
Combine and blend cream cheese, salmon liquid, lemon juice, horseradish and liquid smoke.
Fold in salmon and green onions.
Refrigerate until chilled to allow flavors to meld.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: orange and cherry cobbler
directions: In saucepan, combine pie filling, water and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into a round cake dish.
Top hot cherries with rolls, cut side up.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until rolls are done.
Spread tops with the icing that comes in the orange roll package.
Serve warm.
(Also try peach filling.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed, drain and rinse with cold water. Combine macaroni and other ingredients.
Mix salad dressing and pour over salad.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add brown sugar and Bisquick mix; mix well.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Cake is real chewy.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in the oleo.
In a separate bowl, mix the eggs and corn.
Mix the sauteed onion and pepper with sour cream and corn bread mix.
Add eggs and corn to the mixture and spread in a greased 7 x 12 inch baking dish.
Cover mixture with shredded cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: nuts over pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.

title: fabulous ham and cheese souffle
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Spread half the bread cubes evenly in dish.
Add the ham and both cheeses, then cover with remaining bread cubes.
Mix eggs, milk, onion, salt and mustard.
Pour evenly over bread cubes and refrigerate overnight. Combine corn flakes and butter for a topping.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: pinwheel hash ring
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients.
Unroll each crescent roll.
Place triangles of dough on greased cookie sheet with large ends of each triangle in the middle, overlapping slightly, with small ends pointing outward to edges of cookie sheet.
Effect will be of a large sunburst with open circle in center.
Place hash mixture in ring over base of triangles.
Fold points over filling and tuck under the base of the center with filling showing between slits of the ring.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be served with scrambled eggs, stewed tomatoes or celery soup if desired.

title: no guilt chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 9 inch pie plate, mix chicken, vegetables and soup.
Mix milk, egg and baking mix.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden.

title: doughy white bread
directions: Melt butter and allow to cool.
Follow package directions to activate yeast.
Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Combine with egg. Add butter and milk.
Add yeast last.
Beat well.
Return to bowl and let rise covered for one hour or until doubled.
Shape into two loaves and let rise in pans.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf with piquant sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Drain.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: sugar-free vegetable gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cold water.
Let set until partially thickened.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 4.

title: quick pepper steak
directions: Remove fat from meat and brown.
Cut steak into bite-size pieces.
Add mushrooms and gravy.
Cook noodles and drain.
Serve steak and gravy over noodles.
Excellent with rolls and tossed salad.

title: graham cracker candy
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and Pet milk.
Cook on medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted. Remove from heat and add crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: deviled clams
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and let stand for bread crumbs to absorb liquid.
Mixture should be moist.
Fill the half clam shells.
Sprinkle each with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb strawberry dessert
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1-inch pieces and put into saucepan with sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes.

title: baked alaska
directions: Make cake as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from pan; let completely cool.
Slice cake into 4 pieces. Slice ice cream lengthwise, about the thickness of the cake layers.
On one layer, place ice cream.
Place another layer of cake on top.
This will make two cakes.
Wrap one; freeze it for use later.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add sugar and flavoring.
Spread on one cake.
Bake for 3 minutes, or until brown.
Have oven preheated to 500°.

title: nutty canadian cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses with 2 tablespoons maple syrup. Shape into a ball.
Brush on the remaining syrup and coat with pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: low-fat chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken with garlic salt and paprika and broil.
Stir 1/2 bouillon into cooked rice and place in casserole.
Place chicken on top of rice and pour remaining bouillon over all.
Bake for 1/2 hour in a 325° oven.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until well mixed.
Add buttermilk and yeast. Work into flour with large spoon. Grease a large bowl.
Put in dough. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use. Roll about 1/2-inch thick on a floured surface.
Let rise about 1 1/2 hours. Brush with butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal-chocolate morsel cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: custard pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend 4 to 5 minutes.
You could add raisins or nuts or coconut if you like.
Pour into a greased pie plate and bake for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of pie.
Enjoy!

title: jiffy cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water; mix all ingredients well.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour.
Mix into a soft dough.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Work one half at a time.
Roll out on a floured surface. Sprinkle with a mixture of the cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up from the small end.
Cut into half-inch pieces and put into a greased pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
May be frosted with a drizzle of powdered sugar and milk.

title: b-b-q
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boil.
Add meat and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free banana bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in greased loaf pan.

title: layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the lettuce, celery, peppers, eggs, onion and peas.

title: octopus sauce(salsa di pulpo)
directions: Wash octopus in
salted water, pounding against sink to remove any sand that
may
be
in
suction
cups on tentacles. Rinse and wash again.
Remove head and discard, using only the tentacles. Rinse again
and drain.
In medium saucepan, saute onion in oil until
tender
but
not
brown.
Add
octopus and saute until octopus
curls
and turns pinkish-red.
To octopus add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook on medium-low heat for 1
hour,
stirring occasionally.
Serve
with
spaghetti
or metazanne, cooked according to package directions.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: icing for carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on cake.

title: man sized steak salad
directions: Boil meat at 550° for 13 minutes per side; cool.
Cut into 3/8-inch strips.
Arrange in baking dish (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch). Place mushrooms on meat.
Top with pepper rings.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting
directions: In a small mixer bowl, cream the butter.
Add cocoa and sugar alternately with milk.
Beat to spreading consistency (additional milk may be needed).
Blend in vanilla.
Makes about 2 cups of frosting.

title: fruited macaroni salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar, flour and salt. Drain juice from oranges and pineapple into a 1-cup measuring cup; cover and refrigerate fruit. Add enough water to the juice, if needed, to measure 1 cup; stir into the sugar mixture until smooth. Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.

Reduce heat; cook and stir 1 minute longer. Remove from heat. Stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg; return all to pan, stirring constantly. Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat. In a bowl, combine the macaroni and cooked dressing. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: sweet 'n sour pork
directions: Thinly slice pork into bite-size strips; set aside.
Preheat wok or large skillet to high heat.
Make sauce in a bowl by stirring together teriyaki sauce, cornstarch and seasoning package from frozen vegetables.
Set aside sauce.
Add oil to skillet. Stir-fry pork over heat for about 3 minutes or until it is no longer pink, then remove from skillet.
Add frozen vegetables, undrained pineapple and water to skillet.
Add sauce.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thick and bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes; stir in meat and cook 30 seconds.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: artichoke and basil hero
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine basil, oil, Parmesan cheese, capers, vinegar, mustard and garlic.
Cover; blend until nearly smooth.
Set aside.
Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Hollow out each half, leaving a 1-inch shell.
Spread basil mixture over each half of bread.
On bottom half, layer artichoke hearts, Provolone cheese, tomato and spinach.
Cover with top bread.
Cut sandwich crosswise into 6 to 8 pieces.

title: broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender.
Put in the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In saucepan, melt half of the butter. Blend in flour, salt and a dash of pepper.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Pour over broccoli and onion. Place cheese on top and then use other half of butter; melt and toss bread crumbs in and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a small mixing
bowl beat the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and beat well.
Gradually beat in milk. Fold in the cool whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Freeze until firm.
Wrap in moisture proof wrap.

title: baked clams
directions: Melt butter in frying pan; add clams, crabmeat and bread crumbs.
Refrigerate mix, then prepare in shells (real or aluminum) and bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Add bacon if desired.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Mix together well and press mixture evenly in the bottom of a 9-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Add filling.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Make in rolls or pat down in ice cube trays, lined with waxed paper.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt cocoa in water and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, add buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to mixture and beat.
Pour on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: california blend casserole
directions: In large, glass casserole (cake pan is too big), melt margarine.
Add celery and onion.
Saute on low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add rice.
Stir well.
Add bag of vegetables and mix together.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Serve as side dish.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Add buttermilk.
Grease pan.
Pour in batter.
Butter tops of biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Place cod in pan and pour enough water and chicken broth to cover.
Remove fish and bring liquid to boil.
Add cod; reduce heat to low and simmer about 5 minutes or until cod is opaque and separates easily into large flakes.
Remove fish from liquid and cool.
Flake fish, removing skin and bones.

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Cut crusts on bread.
Put light coat of butter on outside. Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and softened stick of butter. Spread this mixture on each sliced, then roll up.
Make a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle this on outside; freeze.
Bake at 375° for approximately 7 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Simmer together tomatoes, mushroom soup, onion soup and water. Put rice in baking dish.
Set chops on top of rice.
Pour mixture over rice and chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes and then uncover and bake for additional 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oats, water and butter.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix sugars, eggs, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add to oats mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(Mash ripe bananas first.) Grease a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a mixing bowl, mix thoroughly the margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet (vegetable spray works well).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: francis b's salad
directions: Marinate overnight in Wish-Bone Italian dressing. Add raw cauliflower and cherry tomatoes. Shake (toss) and serve.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the 2 cups boiling water; stir gradually into the beaten cream cheese until melted.
Drain oranges, reserving their liquid.
Measure and add enough cold water to equal 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Mix into Jell-O mixture.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat chilled topping mix (Dream Whip) according to directions on package.
Fold into Jell-O mixture along with oranges, nuts and cottage cheese.
Turn into lightly oiled 9 x 13 x 2-inch salad dish or pan.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt for 5 minutes at slow heat.
Do not boil hard.
Remove from heat.
Add soda, pour over popcorn and stir well.
Cook in oven for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: banana smoothie
directions: *With plain yogurt, add 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: debbie's vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out and pat into a 13 x 15-inch cookie sheet the crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese, garlic salt and dill weed.
Dice a few green onions and add to mayonnaise mixture.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chop fine green onions, cauliflower, broccoli, mushrooms, green peppers, tomatoes and black olives.
Sprinkle over crust. Refrigerate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Add milk; stir.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Combine 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; add to peaches.
Spoon mixture over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until browned.

title: broiled icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on top of 9 x 13-inch white or yellow cake while it is still warm.
Place very low under broiler; broil until icing bubbles all over surface and becomes brown.
Take care that it does not burn.

title: lemony chicken nuggets
directions: Measure first 7 ingredients into a plastic bag; close tightly and shake to blend.
Moisten chicken with lemon juice.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Place chicken chunks, a few at a time, into plastic bag.
Shake to coat thoroughly.
Pour oil into heavy saucepan, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat to 375°.
Carefully add chicken, a few pieces at a time.
Fry, turning once, about 2 minutes or until tender.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chipped beef spread(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in shallow baking dish. Microwave 4 to 5 minutes.
Turn 1/4 turn during cooking.
Serve hot as spread for crackers.

title: fillet of flounder florentine
directions: Dip fish in seasoned flour, then in beaten egg to which cheese, parsley, salt and pepper have been added.
Saute in oil or butter until brown.
While fish is sauteing, mix garlic, wine, lemon juice and butter together and bring to boil to evaporate wine, approximately 1/2 minute.
Add cooked spinach to serving dish. (Have spinach warm.)
Lay fish over spinach.
Pour hot mix (garlic, wine, lemon juice, butter) over fish and spinach.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Please, no substitutes.

title: greek tomato salad
directions: Cut tomatoes to bite size.
Cut olives in half.
Rub bowl with garlic; add tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Sprinkle with vinegar and olive oil.
Add seasonings and toss.
Marinate for at least 4 hours on counter.
If longer, store in refrigerate until 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Taste improves the longer it stands at room temperature.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger:
drain.
Rinse with boiling water to remove all grease.
Add to lettuce, tomatoes, onion and Cheddar cheese which have been mixed together well.
Add kidney beans, drained and rinsed.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook the egg noodles until tender; mix in the tuna.
While stirring add chopped onion and mayonnaise and add salt, then add the sweet peas and mix thoroughly.
Let stand for 5 minutes and restir.
It's ready to eat.
This can be served hot or cold!

title: chowder(winning recipe)
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; drain (saving fat).
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Slowly saute onions, green pepper, celery, carrots and garlic in bacon fat until tender.
Boil potatoes in salted water until cooked.
Combine vegetables; add seasonings and beat in a mixer until creamy.
Do not beat longer or it will become too smooth and thick.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Add pumpkin; mix well. Blend in flour, salt, baking powder and spices; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Raisins and/or nuts can be added. Freezes well.
One can pumpkin will make 2 batches.

title: how to make pickles
directions: Heat beans, do not boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour off juice.
While hot, add ingredients.
Marinate 24 hours.
Serve cold.

title: maxine's chicken
directions: Place
chicken flat in baking dish,
salt
and	pepper, chop onion over top.
Mix soups and sherry; pour over chicken. Grate cheese and spread over top.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.	Cook rice according to directions.
Brown small onion
in
part
of bacon grease.
Blend bouillon soup
and
Worcestershire sauce; add in rice.
Add onion and bacon.
Cook
the
last 30 minutes that the chicken cooks.

title: bourbon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together eggs, sugar and butter. Beat corn syrup and bourbon well in a separate bowl.
Add bourbon mixture to egg mixture; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch pie shell and bake 40 to 50 minutes, until set.

title: candied dills
directions: Let 25 pickles (4 inch size) stand 2 weeks in salt brine (9 pt. water, 1 pt. salt). Drain & wash. Cut in chuncks or chips & put in water with Alum - size of walnut (1 heaping Tbsp.). Next morning, wash & drain & pour dressing over pickles.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Slice sausage and brown in oil.
Add onion, carrots and spices.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except for tortellini.
Simmer, covered for 1 hour.
Add tortellini and cook until done.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Serve with rye rounds or cocktail rye bread.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: To make marinade, combine all ingredients except shrimp. Marinate the shrimp for 1/2 to 3 hours.
Broil or barbecue for 3 minutes each side.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.

title: nana's turkey stuffing(mrs. catherine wissman)
directions: Chop cleaned celery into small diced pieces; also dice the onion.
Cut bacon into pieces small enough to crumble when cooked. Combine celery, onion and bacon in large frying pan.
Cook over medium heat until bacon is all crisp.
Drain any fat off and pat with paper towel.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Night before:
Dice wheat and white bread.
Cook celery and onion in margarine until translucent.
Add to cubed bread.
Mix broth, seasoning, egg, salt, pepper together.
Add to cubed bread. Add water as needed so mixture is moist.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Blend soup, flour, sour cream, carrots, onions, salt and pepper.
Then stir in broccoli (2-quart casserole).
Moisten stuffing mix with butter/margarine, then sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Put everything in a big pot and cook slowly for about 3 1/2 hours.

title: cheese delights
directions: Mix and roll in wax paper and place in refrigerator overnight. Slice thin and place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix mayo, yogurt and lemon juice.
Stir with remaining ingredients.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches and 1/2 cup of sugar and set aside.
Set oven to 350°.
Put margarine in deep baking dish and set in oven to melt. Make batter of other ingredients and pour over melted margarine; do not stir.
Put sugared peaches on top of batter; do not stir.
Bake until crust is light brown.
Peaches will sink to bottom.
Can serve ice cream on top.

title: mull cider
directions: Bring to boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices and serve hot.

title: bishop bread
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Blend in dry ingredients, then fold in nuts, dates, chips and cherries.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300°
for 90 minutes.
Be sure to bake long enough.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring once each hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add soup; mix well.
Blend in raisins and nuts. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter soup
directions: Boil chicken stock, onions and celery together for 45 to 60 minutes.
Strain out onion and celery and discard.
Stir in peanut butter until dissolved.
Mix flour with half and half, add together with remaining ingredients, simmer all together 15 minutes.
Add dash of egg shade for coloring.
Garnish with 1/2 teaspoon bacon crumbs or minced country ham.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: swedish pecan balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except powdered sugar, and mix well. Shape dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 275° for about 30 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar after they're cooled.

title: almond crescent cookies(a christmastime favorite)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add almonds and extract. Mix in flour and salt.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Roll into pencil-thin strips, 2 1/2 inches long.
Place 1 inch apart on baking sheets.
Curl into crescents.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on pan.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Mix the pineapple with the cheese.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Mix together the bread crumbs, sugar, flour and melted butter.
Spread on the pineapple mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger mess
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet while potatoes are cooking.
Pour hamburger and onion into saucepan.
Add mushroom soup.
Fill can with milk and add to mixture.
Add potatoes and peas.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: quick cornbread mix
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or two knives to mix thoroughly.
Place mix in a jar or canister and store in a dry place until ready to use.
This mix will keep in a cool place for about a month.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl. Beat in eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature before cutting.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: orange pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add butter and egg yolks, mixing well.
Add milk, juice and rind.
Bake in crust until set at 350°. Use the egg white for meringue.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Beat together sugar, milk, flour and margarine.
Pour into pudding pan.
Spoon fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: white cookies - pink icing
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix and add to buttermilk, soda, baking powder and flour (add gradually).
Cool dough in refrigerator before rolling and cutting with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: cherry crunch(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 8-inch square baking pan. Mix oats, flour and sugar. Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Spoon half of mixture into prepared pan. Top with pie filling. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Spoon into dessert dishes. Serve warm with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Cut up bacon into 1/2-inch square pieces; dice onion.
Combine with ground beef and brown and then drain.
Combine all ingredients except cheese in a medium size roaster.
Do not drain the beans.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 350° oven.
(Fifteen minutes before removing from the oven, sprinkle grated cheese over the top.)
Good served warm or cold.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients with mixer or in blender.
This dressing tastes better if refrigerated for several hours or overnight.

title: cocoa-lace cookies
directions: Spray baking sheets with no-stick cooking spray; set aside.

In medium saucepan melt margarine, stir in brown sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients until blended. Drop mixture by teaspoons 3 inches apart on prepared baking sheets. Bake 9 minutes at 350° or until cookies spread thin and are deep brown (cookies will still be soft).
Cool 2 minutes on sheets. Working quickly with spatula, remove cookies to wire rack; cool completely.
Sprinkle, if desired, with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: mom's stuffed olives
directions: Large green olives with pits are used for this recipe.
With a small paring knife, remove the olive from the pit (pare as you would an apple in corkscrew fashion so you have one continuous piece).
Wrap olive around small ball of meat stuffing.
Roll olive in flour, beaten egg and then bread crumbs (Italian seasoned or plain dry bread crumbs may be used).
Fry slowly, turning to brown all sides evenly.
It's work, but they are always a hit!

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain all the fruit.
In 3-quart baking dish, place peaches and pears with hollow side up.
Place apricots on top.
Sprinkle this with pineapple and cherries.
Combine butter, sugar and curry powder.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste 3 or 4 times.
Cool and refrigerate at least one day.
Heat before serving.

title: ginger syllabub
directions: Mix Advocaat and preserves well together.
Fold into the cream.
Gently transfer into a serving dish.
Put in refrigerator for a few hours.
When set, decorate with a few ginger pieces. Serves 4 to 5.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix it
all together.
Makes 5 quarts of dry mix.
Use 4 teaspoons (heaping) per cup hot water.

title: frost cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and the sifted dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and spread the beaten butter into a baking sheet as thin as possible.

title: chicken-in-a-crock
directions: Dissolve bouillon in hot water. Season chicken with pepper and onion salt.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix soup and bouillon together. Pour over chicken.
Cook on low heat, covered, for approximately 5 hours.
